{"type":"message","id":"a753d1ff","parentId":"760a900c","timestamp":"2026-04-14T05:28:01.036Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see a problem. The wiki-auto-learn.py script is running multiple instances at the same time. Looking at the output, there are 6 concurrent processes all running at the same time (06:41, 07:44, 08:47, 09:50, 10:53, 11:56, 12:58) - these are different hours, so the cron scheduler is spawning a new run every hour, but each run is taking longer than an hour, causing overlap.\n\nActually wait, looking more carefully - the start times show different hours (06:41, 07:44, 08:47, 09:50, 10:53, 11:56, 12:58). \n\nThe wiki-auto-learn cron is set to run every hour, but each execution is overlapping with the next one since they're all still running when the next hour's job starts. I need to check if there's a lock mechanism preventing concurrent runs, look at the cron configuration, and examine the other health metrics like ephemeral data and hook status.","thinkingSignature":"de7875eac7e4f5d7e4b03285326dc0aa88abe243ab079238f32cfc42582e1278"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_swhdly7hgtv2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check cron jobs\ncat /home/ai/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -60"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_swhdly7hgtv2_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check ephemeral data\nls -la /home/ai/.openclaw/memory/ephemeral/ 2>/dev/null | head -10\necho \"---\"\nls /home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/ 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_swhdly7hgtv2_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check skills\nls /home/ai/.openclaw/skills/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":20948,"output":385,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40595,"cost":{"input":0.0062844,"output":0.00046199999999999995,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0079021199999