ning on-message.sh probably isn't sending anything to it.\\n\\nLooking at the HOOK.md, on-message.sh should be triggered by message events through a separate context-hook.js mechanism. I need to check if that's actually configured and working. The log.md is also cluttered with auto-cycle entries every 10 seconds, though that should stop now that the old process is gone. The session directory shows zero message history for the current session, which suggests the session might not have persisted properly.\\n\\nThe session summary hook should have written something when the session started, but the current session at `agent=main=main` only has the context.json that was just modified. I'm trying to figure out if this is actually the session created by the /new command or if it's a different one, since the session structure seems unclear.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"c5c2204f8471d6a6caf795e1899bb9e768dcfe6491ca3d5a2033654335e27abb\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_p91x6tcxgerj_1\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"echo \\\"=== session 目录详情 ===\\\"\\nls -la ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent\\\\:main\\\\:main/\\necho \\\"\\\"\\nls ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent\\\\:main\\\\:main/ | head -10\\n\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== runtime session key ===\\\"\\necho \\\"agent=main=main\\\"\\n\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== session 创建时间 ===\\\"\\nstat ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent\\\\:main\\\\:main/ | grep -E \\\"Birth|Modify\\\"\"}}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":41316,\"output\":705,\"cacheRead\":18887,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":60908,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.0123948,\"output\":0.000846,\"cacheRead\":0.0011332199999999999,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.014374019999999998}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1776072947202,\"responseId\":\"062bebf2c0abb4be36982ab58d9d3186\"}}\n/home/ai/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/d263827d-6dd2-4f5a-84d7-68ae11ee9e16.jsonl.reset.2026-04-13T12-11-13.150Z:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"bd6b592d\",\"parentId\":\"3e42e245\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-13T09:38:21.901Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"All three (3105, 3103, 3104) are on 0.0.0.0 (all interfaces), so network namespace shouldn't be an issue. They're all on the same machine.\\n\\nThe context.json issue remains a mystery without being able to see the gateway's internal state. Let me just document it as a known bug and move on.\\n\\nNow let me compile my complete critical review. I'll be systematic and thorough.\\n\\n**COMPLETE CRITICAL REVIEW:**\\n\\n**🔴 CRITICAL - Auto-score-classify classification 持续 null**\\n- 问题：context.json 中 `classification` 字段始终为 null，但 `scoring` 正常\\n\\n\\n- 证据：context.json 多次更新（17:04、17:17、17:30），scoring 有效值，classification 始终 null\\n- 验证：3105 API 本身正常（curl 和 node 测试均通过）\\n- 根因：gateway 进程内 hook 执行时，对 3105 的 HTTP 请求失败，但 3103 成功\\n- 可能原因：gateway 缓存了旧版 hook 代码（3108）或 3105 在 hook 执行时响应异常\\n\\n**🟡 MEDIUM - on-message.sh 从未发送过消息**\\n- 问题：context-api 在 3101 上始终为空，messages 为 0\\n- on-message.sh 指向已弃用的 18790 端口（已改为 3101）\\n- 即使修复后，context-api 仍然没有收到消息，这说明 gateway 可能根本没有调用这个 hook\\n\\n**🟡 MEDIUM - openclaw-router (pid 434) 完全空闲**\\n- 问题：context-api 在 3101 端口一直没有消息进来\\n\\n，说明 openclaw-router 的上下文功能从未被真正使用过\\n- 应该调查 gateway 是否真的在用这个端点，还是它本身就是冗余的\\n\\n**🟢 LOW - session-summary 链路从未真正验证**\\n- session-summary hook 在 /new 时生成摘要，bootstrap hook 读取并注入到新 session\\n- 但实际上还没有发生过一次完整的链路传输\\n\\n，手动创建的 session-summary 只是临时的替代方案\\n\\n**🟢 LOW - session 目录结构异常**\\n- `agent=main=main` 目录只有 context.json，缺少 message history JSONL 文件\\n- 这可能只是设计差异，不代表有问题\\n\\n**🟢 LOW - memory/log.md 包含过时的 auto-cycle 条目**\\n- 这些是 wiki-auto-learn.py 的旧日志，虽然已被杀掉，但文件本身还没清理\\n\\n我应该在报告中明确指出这些问题的优先級和影响范围，而不是继续猜测根本原因。\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"3276147eeec4598073d4310cac706c70b683b36f7ceec7dc89000cc01a26b7ec\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"评审完成。开始汇报。\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🔴 严重问题（影响核心功能）\\n\\n**1. auto-score-classify：classification 持续 null，链路不通**\\n\\n证据：\\n```\\ncontext.json（17:30:59 最新写入）\\n  classification: null  ← 每次都是 null\\n  scoring: { score: 24 }  ← 有值\\n  timestamp: 2026-04-13T09:30:59.115Z\\n  messagePreview: \\\"犀利、严格的进行评审、检查\\\"\\n```\\n\\n验证结果：\\n- `curl → 3105/classify`：**200 正常返回**\\n- `node fetchJSON → 3105/classify`：**OK，scene=clarify**\\n- hook 写入 context.json：**classification 永远是 null**\\n\\n结论：3105 API 本身正常，但 **hook 运行时对 3105 的请求静默失败**。gateway 进程内 http.request 到 3105 返回 null，但 3103 成功。可能是：\\n- gateway 缓存了旧版 hook 代码（3108 未修复）\\n- gateway 进程网络策略差异\\n\\n---\\n\\n**2. on-message.sh：0 条消息，hook 从未被触发**\\n\\n```\\ncontext-api 状态（3101）：\\n  {\\\"messages\\\":0,\\\"chars\\\":0}  ← 从未收到过消息\\n```\\n\\non-message.sh 原本指向废弃的 18790（已改为 3101），但改完还是 0 条。gateway 似乎根本没有对每条消息调用这个 hook。\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🟡 中等问题\\n\\n**3. openclaw-router (pid 434) 完全空闲**\\n\\ncontext-api.js 在 3101 监听，运行至今 0 条消息。gateway 没有向它推送任何 context。如果这个组件本来就没被接入，就是废弃进程。\\n\\n**4. session-summary 链路从未真正验证**\\n\\n理论上：`ephemeral → session-summary hook → bootstrap hook → 新session`\\n\\n实际上：\\n- session-summary hook **从未运行过**（没看到它生成的摘要文件）\\n- bootstrap hook **注入了手写的替代摘要**（非真实链路产出）\\n- **真正从未验证过**\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🟢 低优先级\\n\\n**5. session 目录缺少 message history JSONL**\\n\\n`~/.openclaw/sessions/agent=main=main/` 只有 context.json（463字节），无 `.jsonl` 消息历史文件。webchat session 消息可能存在 gateway 内部数据库，不在文件系统。\\n\\n**6. memory/log.md 残留 auto-cycle 日志**\\n\\nwiki-auto-learn.py 的旧日志还在，每 10 秒一条占空间，不过进程已清理。\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 优先级处理建议\\n\\n| 优先级 | 问题 | 处理 |\\n|--------|------|------|\\n| **P0** | classification null | 需在 gateway 进程内直接调试，或重启 gateway 强制重载 hook |\\n| **P1** | on-message.sh 从不触发 | 确认 gateway 是否真的会调用 message hook |\\n| **P2** | openclaw-router 废弃 | 确认用途后关闭或清理 |\\n| **P3** | session-summary 链路验证 | 下次 /new 时检查 bootstrap 是否注入真实摘要 |\\n\\n[[reply_to_current]] 总结：框架基础设施（cron、entities、ephemeral）正常运转，但**两个核心 hook 存在静默失败**——classification 拿不到数据，context-api 从未收到消息。这些是系统性断点。\"}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":45210,\"output\":1231,\"cacheRead\":18887,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":65328,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.013562999999999999,\"output\":0.0014772,\"cacheRead\":0.0011332199999999999,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.016173419999999997}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1776073053098,\"responseId\":\"062bec5d04eca7d09345b67bd9404081\"}}\n/home/ai/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/d263827d-6dd2-4f5a-84d7-68ae11ee9e16.jsonl.reset.2026-04-13T12-11-13.150Z:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"20616a67\",\"parentId\":\"4bf19674\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-13T09:41:50.236Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"System (untrusted): [2026-04-13 17:35:47 GMT+8] Exec completed (glow-sho, code 1) :: === wiki-auto-learn.py 进程 === === cron job 实际命令 === b3c6834e-c671-4b21-b6d4-0dc9c86f0e84 wiki-learn cron 0 * * * * @ Asia/Shangha... in 27m 33m ago ok isolated main - 63a6537d-619…\\n\\nSender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Mon 2026-04-13 17:41 GMT+8] 跑通\"}],\"timestamp\":1776073310226}}\n/home/ai/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/d263827d-6dd2-4f5a-84d7-68ae11ee9e16.jsonl.reset.2026-04-13T12-11-13.150Z:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"8781222e\",\"parentId\":\"df9a9cf6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-13T10:49:45.975Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Now I can see what happened:\\n- 18:01: auto-cycle (old wiki-auto-learn.py) ran and said \\\"sources:35\\\"\\n- 18:02: wiki-learn-once.sh ran and pruned to 30 (entities:30, new:0, skip:13)\\n\\nBut the current entities count shows 41! So something happened AFTER 18:02. The old wiki-auto-learn.py was still running at 18:01 and adding entities!\\n\\nLook: \\\"auto-cycle | iter 2 | sources:35\\\" - this is the old wiki-auto-learn.py script, not wiki-learn-once.sh. \\n\\nIt was adding entities! And it ran AFTER we thought we killed all the wiki-auto-learn.py processes. The cron at 18:00 must have triggered it. Looking at the cron job definition, the message tells the isolated LLM to execute wiki-learn-once.sh and append output to log.md, but somewhere the old wiki-auto-learn.py process is still running and interfering with the new script's work.\\n\\nThe \\\"auto-cycle\\\" entries show the old wiki-auto-learn.py was active from 16:09 to 18:01, which means it wasn't properly killed or a new instance started after our cleanup. The cron job message just tells the LLM to run the script, but if the LLM is interpreting this differently or if there's a background process still executing the old script, that would explain why we're seeing 41 entities instead of the expected count. Looking at the execution logs more carefully, I see the issue now - the blocklist had only 9 entries at 18:02, so the 13 skipped entries represent the 9 blocklisted skills plus 4 others that the script decided to skip for other reasons, which accounts for the discrepancy between what was added and what should have been skipped.\\n\\nBut then we jump to 41 entities somehow, and I think the culprit is that old wiki-auto-learn.py process - it was still running at 18:01, which means it was actively modifying the entities between our cleanup at 17:00 and when the new script finally ran at 18:02.\\n\\nLet me trace through what happened: at 16:57 we had 35 entities after pruning, then between 16:57 and 18:01 the old script kept adding more, and by 18:01 it reported 35 again but had actually grown beyond that. The cron at 18:00 triggered the new script which should have reset things to 30, but something went wrong.\\n\\nLooking at the blocklist now showing 19 entries suggests the script was somehow adding to it incrementally rather than replacing it, which would explain the entity count explosion and why the pruning didn't stick.\\n\\nThe 18:02 run shows \\\"entities:30 | new:0 | skip:13\\\", which indicates no new entities were added, but then we jump to 41 by 18:46 - that's a 9-11 entity increase in 44 minutes, which shouldn't happen if the new script is actually running and respecting the blocklist. Something is still adding entities outside the control of the current script.\\n\\nLooking back at the 17:10 run more carefully, I see \\\"entities:35 | new:10\\\" meaning 10 new entities were added while 14 were skipped for space, but the blocklist only grew from 9 to 13 (4 new entries). That means 6 pruned entities weren't recorded in the blocklist - they came from the initial cleanup at 17:00 when we had 16 auto-ingested entities removed. The blocklist was only tracking what was pruned during that specific cleanup, not everything that got removed. I need to reconsider how the blocklist gets populated. Looking at the code, it only adds entries when skills are pruned via `blocklist_add`, not when they're removed during initial cleanup. So the blocklist should have grown to 16 after `prune_to_target` ran at 16:12, but it only shows 9—which means either the cleanup happened before blocklist was initialized, or the blocklist logic wasn't triggered the way I thought.\\n\\nLet me trace through what happened: at 17:00 I deleted all auto-ingested entities manually, then ran the script which added 10 and removed 11, ending at 30 with blocklist at 9. The old script must have kept running and adding more auto-ingested entities, pushing the count to 41 by 18:01. When the new script finally ran at 18:02, it added 0 new ones and showed 30 entities, so the blocklist only captured those 9 entries from the previous pruning cycle. After that, something continued to add entities—the old wiki-auto-learn.py process was still running at 18:01 and kept inserting more auto-ingested entities. Even though the cron job specifies the new script should run, if there's a background process repeatedly executing the old wiki-auto-learn.py with `--mode=ingest --limit=3`, that could be adding entities beyond what the cron job itself does. I should just kill any remaining wiki-auto-learn.py processes and run the cleanup script again to stabilize at 30.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"1f50536a672a152621c36808ae7fb50a2920d8ff3f2b8a735384abd195e9b40c\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_73pealsggedj_1\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"echo \\\"=== wiki-auto-learn 进程 ===\\\"\\nps aux | grep \\\"wiki-auto-learn\\\\|wiki-7h-loop\\\\|wiki-learn\\\" | grep -v grep\\n\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== 确认当前 entities ===\\\"\\nls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/ | wc -l\"}}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":71801,\"output\":1141,\"cacheRead\":18895,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":91837,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.0215403,\"output\":0.0013691999999999999,\"cacheRead\":0.0011336999999999999,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.0240432}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1776077351411,\"responseId\":\"062bfd26620a866a5b236acc8d26249d\"}}\n/home/ai/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/d263827d-6dd2-4f5a-84d7-68ae11ee9e16.jsonl.reset.2026-04-13T12-11-13.150Z:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"6c5afd62\",\"parentId\":\"0c4bdcce\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-13T10:49:52.620Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"There it is. The old wiki-auto-learn.py is STILL running (pid 145709, started at 17:56!). It was started after our cleanup at 17:00. This process is the reason entities grew from 30 to 41. It keeps adding 3 entities every time it runs.\\n\\nLet me kill it and also kill any other instances. Then clean up entities back to 30 and restart the gateway to make sure the hook changes take effect.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"b759bf3bef1cbc9a67a8604c24071c9bbd392ff029235f328e3e1a811ebab7f3\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"找到了。**旧的 wiki-auto-learn.py 还在跑（pid 145709，17:56 启动）**，一直在往 entities 加东西。\\n\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_zxoie3lp2p0z_1\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"com