ra 10 came from. The cron at 18:02 added 10 to reach 35, then my manual run at 18:50 kept it at 35. But between 18:50 and now, something must have added another 10. Let me look at the cron schedule - it runs at :02 every hour in Asia/Shanghai, so there should've been another run at 19:02, but that would be after 18:59. Unless there's something else running that's adding these entities.\\n\\nActually, I need to look at the process list more carefully. The grep command with a space after \\\"wiki\\\" would've matched more than just the python processes - it would've caught the grep itself. So the 3 residual processes might not be python processes at all.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"19586e81a8b910ea6f02c7ae18c58c34660370b7b736ad43832b8448c4e1731d\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_sj3p14dkaex3_1\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"echo \\\"=== 真正在跑的相关进程 ===\\\"\\nps aux | grep -E \\\"python|node|bash\\\" | grep -v grep | grep -v \\\"snap\\\\|systemd\\\" | head -15\\n\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== cron 下次运行 ===\\\"\\n~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw cron list 2>/dev/null | grep -A1 \\\"wiki-learn\\\" | head -3\"}}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":80529,\"output\":614,\"cacheRead\":18895,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":100038,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.024158699999999998,\"output\":0.0007368,\"cacheRead\":0.0011336999999999999,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.0260292}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1776078050515,\"responseId\":\"062bffe2d3f83cf90ec59ef044f5f2b9\"}}\n/home/ai/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/d263827d-6dd2-4f5a-84d7-68ae11ee9e16.jsonl.reset.2026-04-13T12-11-13.150Z:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"98e5777b\",\"parentId\":\"0344c3e7\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-13T11:02:13.513Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"systemctl failed because we're not running as root in this environment. But we successfully