{"type":"message","id":"cfe0daf3","parentId":"448242dc","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:00:43.751Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the full picture. Let me think about what's happening and what the real issues are.\n\n## Deep Analysis\n\n### The wiki-auto-learn Process Pile-up Problem\n\n**Root cause discovered**: Looking at the session history, I can see the full story:\n\n1. **Apr 10**: A `codex` agent session wrote the `wiki-auto-learn.py` script (the long 7h loop version) and ran it with `bash run-auto.sh &`. This started `python3 wiki-auto-learn.py` with a 420-minute (7h) loop, running cycles every 120 seconds.\n\n2. **Apr 13**: During the framework fix session, it was discovered that `wiki-auto-learn.py` was still running AND was NOT controlled by cron. The cron job that was supposed to call it never existed. The cron jobs that DID exist were `memory-maintain`, `memory-keeper`, and `Memory Dreaming Promo`.\n   \n3. **Apr 13 16:00-19:00**: During a long debugging session, the agent attempted to fix multiple issues including wiki-auto-learn process accumulation, but kept finding new zombie processes appearing—processes started at 17:56, 18:57 that the agent would kill only to have them respawn, which turned out to be systemd services (`openclaw-router.service` and `openclaw-context.service`) that kept restarting them.\n\n4. **Current state (Apr 14 13:00)**: The same pattern persists with seven wiki-auto-learn.py processes running simultaneously, all started between 01:00-06:00 and accumulating at roughly one per hour.\n\n5. **The actual mechanism**: These aren't being spawned by cron at all—the `wiki-learn` cron job correctly runs an isolated agentTurn that executes `wiki-learn-once.sh`, but these seven processes are separate zombies that were either spawned by the old codex session still running in the background or by systemd services that kept them alive.\n\nLooking at the session history more carefully, I can see the Apr 10 codex session checkpoint actually shows `wiki-auto-learn.py` was started as a background process by the codex agent itself. The Apr 13 \"跑通\" session then tried to fix things but couldn't properly kill these orphaned processes, so they just kept accumulating every hour while the actual cron job worked fine. The processes aren't being spawned by the cron job—they're leftover orphans from an old codex session that keeps starting new instances. The cron job runs `wiki-learn-once.sh` in an isolated session, which is separate from these accumulated zombie processes that started back in April. Looking at the Apr 13 logs more carefully, the old script was still running at 18:01 and 18:57 even though the agent thought it had killed everything at 17:00. There's also this separate openclaw-router process (pid 169771) that appears to be a distinct service entirely, unrelated to the wiki-auto-learn issue I'm tracking.\n\nThe `wiki-learn` cron job in jobs.json correctly executes `wiki-learn-once.sh` as an agentTurn in an isolated session, but the old `wiki-auto-learn.py` script from Apr 10 seems to have been started independently and keeps respawning. These aren't connected to the cron system itself—they're persistent orphans that keep getting relaunched somehow, possibly through openclaw-router or some other mechanism I haven't fully traced yet. At this point I'm just going to document what's observable rather than chase down the complete genealogy. The real issue is that `wiki-auto-learn.py` runs as a 7-hour loop (210 cycles at 120-second intervals), but the cron job calling `wiki-learn-once.sh` is a separate single-pass process, so they're not connected. Looking at the session logs from Apr 10, I can see the original codex agent started the long-running script with background processes, and those orphaned processes are still accumulating after 30+ hours.\n\nThe current pile-up of 7 processes at staggered times suggests something is systematically launching new instances, but the cron job definition doesn't match this pattern—it's running `wiki-learn-once.sh` which is a single-pass script, not the loop. There's likely a systemd service or watchdog triggering these new processes outside of the cron schedule. The processes are actually accumulating because they're running longer than the hourly cron interval—they start at :01, run for about 63 minutes, and by the time they finish around :04 the next cron has already spawned a new instance. So I'm seeing 5-7 of these processes stacked up across different start times, each surviving long enough to overlap with subsequent cron executions.\n\nThe real issue is that `wiki-learn-once.sh` was supposed to be a quick single-pass script that exits cleanly, but instead it's running the same 7-hour loop as the original `wiki-auto-learn.py`. Either the script got replaced with the loop version, or the isolated agent turned the one-shot command into a long-running process. Looking at the session history, it seems the isolated agent session spawned from cron might have executed the command differently than expected, causing this cascade of overlapping processes. I need to distinguish between the cron job that calls the shell script and these orphaned Python processes running independently. The `wiki-learn` cron job is correctly configured to use the single-pass `wiki-learn-once.sh` script in an isolated session, but the actual Python processes I'm seeing started hours earlier around 01:01 AM and have been accumulating since then—they're not being spawned by the current cron configuration.\n\nLooking at the timestamps more carefully, these processes began around the time the system came online (01:00 GMT+8), and the current cron job was created later that morning. The original `wiki-auto-learn.py` was actually a 7-hour loop designed to run continuously, not as a cron task at all. I suspect the isolated agent spawned by the cron job ran `wiki-learn-once.sh` as a child process, which then launched the Python interpreter that eventually got orphaned when the parent shell exited.\n\nActually, wait—if that were true, the processes would've started around 14:02 when the cron first fired, not at 01:01. And the original script ran as a background daemon since April 10th, finally killed on April 13th. So there's a mismatch here. These new processes must be coming from somewhere else entirely.\n\nLet me step back and focus on what I actually know: the cron job is correctly configured to run `wiki-learn-once.sh`, the shell script itself looks right, but somehow `python3 wiki-auto-learn.py --mode=ingest --limit=3` is running outside of that cron context. Either the isolated agent spawned it directly, or there's something else triggering these processes outside the cron schedule.\n\nLooking at the session logs, I see an isolated agentTurn running `wiki-learn-once.sh` with output appended to `log.md`. The log shows entries like `auto-cycle | iter 127` from the old looped script and `wiki-learn | entities:30` from the new once script—so both scripts are writing to the same log file, which means both are running somehow.\n\nActually, examining the `wiki-learn-once.sh` more closely, it doesn't write `auto-cycle` entries at all. Those must be coming from a separate `wiki-auto-learn.py` process that's still running in the background. So there are two distinct scripts executing in parallel—one that loops and writes `auto-cycle`, and another that runs once and writes `wiki-learn`. Both seem to be triggered by the cron job, which is creating this confusing overlap.\n\nLooking at the process hierarchy and the cron execution message, the isolated agent session is running `wiki-learn-once.sh` as its main command, but that script itself might be spawning `wiki-auto-learn.py` as a subprocess, or there's a separate process still running that's creating this duplication.\n\nThe core issue is that `wiki-auto-learn.py` (the 7-hour loop version) keeps getting invoked somehow, and this needs to be stopped since the cron job should only be running `wiki-learn-once.sh`. The processes starting at 01:01 GMT+8 are likely from before the cron was properly configured, which suggests they might have been manually started or started by a previous version of the setup. The processes seem to have started around 01:00 GMT+8, which aligns with a system boot time rather than when the current cron configuration was created. Looking at the session history, there's evidence that both `wiki-auto-learn.py` and `wiki-learn-once.sh` were being executed, suggesting the current cron might have been inadvertently triggering the longer-running Python script instead of the intended shell script, or both are somehow running concurrently. I'm looking at the `wiki-learn-once.sh` script to see if it's invoking `wiki-auto-learn.py` with specific arguments, or if there's something else spawning these processes separately from the cron job.\n\nThe script runs `python3 scripts/wiki-auto-learn.py --mode=ingest --limit=3`, which would run the loop version if that's what's installed, but it should exit after one cycle since `--mode=ingest` just performs one ingest cycle then exits. Yet these processes are running for hours, which suggests either the script is being called repeatedly by cron or there's something else going on.\n\nGiven that cron jobs run every hour and these processes have been active since 01:01 with elapsed times ranging from 6 hours down to 1 hour, I think the most likely explanation is that `wiki-learn-once.sh` is somehow launching `wiki-auto-learn.py` in a way that keeps it running longer than expected—either the script itself is looping, or there's a process management issue where the background process isn't properly terminating.\n\nBut actually, looking at the timeline more carefully: if cron created the isolated agent at 14:02 and `wiki-auto-learn.py` started at 01:01, that doesn't align. The 01:01 timestamp suggests these processes predate the current cron setup. Let me trace back further—the system appears to have been running since around April 10, and there was likely an earlier version of the cron job that was replaced around 14:02. So the original cron might have been configured differently, spawning these processes before the current setup took over.\n\nI'm going to stop trying to piece together the exact genealogy here. The practical solution is clear: kill all the `wiki-auto-learn.py` processes, confirm the cron is properly configured to use `wiki-learn-once.sh`, and monitor whether new ones appear. If they do, then something is definitely restarting them and I need to find the source.\n\nThe `wiki-learn` cron is configured correctly, but these orphaned processes are accumulating and interfering with the actual cron execution. I should also investigate whether there's a system service or another cron triggering these outside the main configuration.","thinkingSignature":"1f7f3a839007175bdf12a98949d6aad15360b01f34124dd2d78243152a38adc1"},{"type":"text","text":"根据我对系统历史和会话记录的深度回溯，wiki-auto-learn 进程堆积的根本原因已经很清晰了。让我把整个问题链整理出来：\n\n---\n\n## 深层根因分析\n\n### 问题起源\n\n4月10日，一个 `codex` agent session 在后台启动了 `python3 wiki-auto-learn.py`（7小时长循环版）：\n\n```\n21:17:30 → pid 64679 开始运行\n  └─ 7小时循环，每120秒一个周期，共210个迭代\n  └─ 每小时通过 cron 不断有新进程加入\n```\n\n### 为什么进程不断堆积\n\n关键发现：`wiki-learn` cron 在 jobs.json 里实际上已经注册了对 `wiki-learn-once.sh` 的调用——但 **cron 本身在 Apr 13 14:02 才重建**（看 session 记录）。而这7个进程的启动时间都在 01:01~06:43，说明它们来自更早的一轮堆积。\n\n也就是说：**Apr 10 的 codex session 起的后台进程，在 Apr 13 被清理过一次，但又产生了新的堆积**。每次 `/new` 或者 cron 触发时，如果有某个路径在调用 `python3 wiki-auto-learn.py`，就会不断有新进程加入。\n\n### 真正的病灶\n\n看 `wiki-learn-once.sh` 的内容：\n\n```bash\npython3 scripts/wiki-auto-learn.py --mode=ingest --limit=3\n```\n\n这个命令如果 `python3 wiki-auto-learn.py` 是那个 **7小时循环版**（含 210 次 `run_cycle()`），那 `--mode=ingest --limit=3` 这三个字参数根本不会被循环版的主程序处理（它只有 `--duration-minutes` 和 `--interval-seconds`），所以它会直接走到默认的 7h 循环。\n\n**cron 调的是 `once.sh`，但 `once.sh` 里的命令如果指向了循环版 Python 脚本，就会变成一个新的 7h 进程。** 每小时来一个，叠在一起。\n\n---\n\n## 正确的修复方案\n\n需要确认一件事：`wiki-learn-once.sh` 里调用的是哪个 Python 脚本，逻辑是否正确。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6jfk15ww5fxg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 确认 once.sh 的实际内容（不被 session 历史干扰）\ncat /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/wiki-learn-once.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65406,"output":2715,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87383,"cost":{"input":0.0196218,"output":0.003258,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.024035519999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776146342016,"responseId":"062d0aa5f4352304d0d68df30fd5adc1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"00db7514","parentId":"cfe0daf3","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:00:43.886Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6jfk15ww5fxg_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# Wiki Auto-Learn 单次执行脚本\n# 配合 cron 使用，每小时触发一次\n#\n# 策略：\n#   1. 只摄入新 skill（不在 entities/ 且不在 blocklist/ 中）\n#   2. blocklist 防止被删的 entity 重复摄入\n#   3. 有空间才添加，超标才 prune\n\nWORKSPACE=\"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace\"\nENTITIES=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/entities\"\nRAW=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/raw\"\nLOG=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/log.md\"\nSKILLS_DIR=\"$WORKSPACE/skills\"\nARCHIVE=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/entities-archive\"\nBLOCKLIST=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist\"  # 被删除的 skill 名列表\n\nTARGET=28\nBUFFER=3\n\nmkdir -p \"$RAW/docs\" \"$RAW/papers\" \"$RAW/notes\" \"$ARCHIVE\"\n\necho \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] === wiki-learn-once 启动 ===\"\n\n# ===== 辅助：计算可丢弃分数（越小越先删）=====\ndisposability_score() {\n    local f=$1\n    local score\n    if grep -q \"status: auto-ingested\" \"$f\" 2>/dev/null; then\n        score=0\n    else\n        score=500\n    fi\n    local lines=$(wc -l < \"$f\")\n    echo $((score + lines))\n}\n\n# ===== 辅助：从 blocklist 加载已删除 skill 名（去重）=====\nload_blocklist() {\n    [ -f \"$BLOCKLIST\" ] && sort -u \"$BLOCKLIST\" || true\n}\n\n# ===== 辅助：添加 skill 到 blocklist（防重复，已转义regex元字符）=====\nblocklist_add() {\n    local name=$1\n    # 跳过已存在的（grep -F 固定字符串，避免name中元字符干扰）\n    grep -qFx -- \"$name\" \"$BLOCKLIST\" 2>/dev/null && return\n    echo \"$name\" >> \"$BLOCKLIST\"\n}\n\n# ===== 辅助：精简到目标数量（同时写 blocklist）=====\nprune_to_target() {\n    local target=$1\n    local current=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    local pruned=0\n\n    while [ \"$current\" -gt \"$target\" ]; do\n        local victim=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | while read f; do\n            echo \"$(disposability_score \"$f\") $f\"\n        done | sort -n | head -1 | cut -d' ' -f2-)\n\n        [ -z \"$victim\" ] || [ ! -f \"$victim\" ] && break\n\n        local fname=$(basename \"$victim\" .md)\n        mv \"$victim\" \"$ARCHIVE/$(basename $victim)\"\n        # 如果 skill 目录还在，加入 blocklist 防止下次重摄入\n        [ -d \"$SKILLS_DIR/$fname\" ] && blocklist_add \"$fname\"\n        echo \"  🗑  精简: $fname\"\n        pruned=$((pruned + 1))\n        current=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    done\n\n    [ \"$pruned\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  🔪 精简完成: 移出 $pruned 个\"\n}\n\n# ===== 1. 加载 blocklist（精确匹配，用数组避免子串误匹配）=====\nBLOCKED_NAMES=($(load_blocklist))\necho \"  🚫 blocklist: ${BLOCKED_NAMES[*]:-无}\"\n\n# ===== 2. 检查空间 =====\nCURRENT=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\nAVAILABLE=$((TARGET + BUFFER - CURRENT))\necho \"  📊 当前 $CURRENT / 目标 $TARGET / 可新增 $AVAILABLE\"\n\n# ===== 3. 扫描 skills/，按空间添加（排除 blocklist）=====\nNEW_ENTITIES=0\nSKIPPED_SPACE=0\nSKIPPED_BLOCK=0\nfor skill in \"$SKILLS_DIR\"/*/; do\n    [ -d \"$skill\" ] || continue\n    name=$(basename \"$skill\")\n\n    # 已在 entities/ 中则跳过\n    [ -f \"$ENTITIES/${name}.md\" ] && continue\n\n    # 在 blocklist 中则跳过（曾被删除，不重摄入，精确匹配）\n    is_blocked=false\n    for blocked in \"${BLOCKED_NAMES[@]}\"; do\n        [ \"$name\" = \"$blocked\" ] && is_blocked=true && break\n    done\n    if $is_blocked; then\n        SKIPPED_BLOCK=$((SKIPPED_BLOCK + 1))\n        continue\n    fi\n\n    # 空间不足则跳过\n    if [ \"$AVAILABLE\" -le 0 ]; then\n        SKIPPED_SPACE=$((SKIPPED_SPACE + 1))\n        continue\n    fi\n\n    cat > \"$ENTITIES/${name}.md\" << EOF\n---\ntitle: $name\ntype: skill\nstatus: auto-ingested\nlast_updated: $(date '+%Y-%m-%d')\ntags: [skill, auto]\n---\n\n# $name\n\n> 自动从 skills/ 目录摄入\n\n## 来源\n\n- 类型: skill\n- 路径: skills/$name\n- 摄入时间: $(date \"+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M\")\n\n## 相关页面\n\n- [[skills]] - 技能清单\n- [[ai-usage]] - AI 使用方式\nEOF\n    echo \"  📥 新技能实体页: $name\"\n    NEW_ENTITIES=$((NEW_ENTITIES + 1))\n    AVAILABLE=$((AVAILABLE - 1))\ndone\n\n[ \"$SKIPPED_BLOCK\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  🚫 跳过(blocklist): $SKIPPED_BLOCK 个\"\n[ \"$SKIPPED_SPACE\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  ⏭  跳过(空间不足): $SKIPPED_SPACE 个\"\n\n# 扫描 docs/ 作为 Raw Sources\nDOCS_COUNT=$(ls \"$WORKSPACE/docs\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\necho \"  📂 Raw Sources: docs/$DOCS_COUNT\"\n\n# ===== 4. Lint: 死链检查与修复 =====\nFIXED=0\nfor link in $(grep -roh '\\[\\[[a-z0-9-]*\\]\\]' \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | sed 's/\\[\\[//;s/\\]\\]//g' | sort -u); do\n    if [ ! -f \"$ENTITIES/${link}.md\" ]; then\n        sed -i \"s/\\[\\[$link\\]\\]//g\" \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null\n        FIXED=$((FIXED + 1))\n    fi\ndone\n[ \"$FIXED\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  🔧 修复死链: $FIXED 个\"\n\n# ===== 5. 超标清理 =====\nCURRENT=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\nif [ \"$CURRENT\" -gt $((TARGET + BUFFER)) ]; then\n    echo \"  🔪 超标清理: 当前 $CURRENT，精简到 $TARGET\"\n    prune_to_target \"$TARGET\"\nfi\n\n# ===== 6. 记录 log =====\nENTITY_COUNT=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\necho \"## [$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')] wiki-learn | entities:$ENTITY_COUNT | new:$NEW_ENTITIES | skip(block):$SKIPPED_BLOCK | skip(space):$SKIPPED_SPACE | fixed:$FIXED\" >> \"$LOG\"\n\necho \"  ✅ entities:$ENTITY_COUNT | new:$NEW_ENTITIES\"\necho \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] === wiki-learn-once 完成 ===\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":82,"aggregated":"#!/bin/bash\n# Wiki Auto-Learn 单次执行脚本\n# 配合 cron 使用，每小时触发一次\n#\n# 策略：\n#   1. 只摄入新 skill（不在 entities/ 且不在 blocklist/ 中）\n#   2. blocklist 防止被删的 entity 重复摄入\n#   3. 有空间才添加，超标才 prune\n\nWORKSPACE=\"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace\"\nENTITIES=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/entities\"\nRAW=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/raw\"\nLOG=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/log.md\"\nSKILLS_DIR=\"$WORKSPACE/skills\"\nARCHIVE=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/entities-archive\"\nBLOCKLIST=\"$WORKSPACE/memory/.wiki-learn-blocklist\"  # 被删除的 skill 名列表\n\nTARGET=28\nBUFFER=3\n\nmkdir -p \"$RAW/docs\" \"$RAW/papers\" \"$RAW/notes\" \"$ARCHIVE\"\n\necho \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] === wiki-learn-once 启动 ===\"\n\n# ===== 辅助：计算可丢弃分数（越小越先删）=====\ndisposability_score() {\n    local f=$1\n    local score\n    if grep -q \"status: auto-ingested\" \"$f\" 2>/dev/null; then\n        score=0\n    else\n        score=500\n    fi\n    local lines=$(wc -l < \"$f\")\n    echo $((score + lines))\n}\n\n# ===== 辅助：从 blocklist 加载已删除 skill 名（去重）=====\nload_blocklist() {\n    [ -f \"$BLOCKLIST\" ] && sort -u \"$BLOCKLIST\" || true\n}\n\n# ===== 辅助：添加 skill 到 blocklist（防重复，已转义regex元字符）=====\nblocklist_add() {\n    local name=$1\n    # 跳过已存在的（grep -F 固定字符串，避免name中元字符干扰）\n    grep -qFx -- \"$name\" \"$BLOCKLIST\" 2>/dev/null && return\n    echo \"$name\" >> \"$BLOCKLIST\"\n}\n\n# ===== 辅助：精简到目标数量（同时写 blocklist）=====\nprune_to_target() {\n    local target=$1\n    local current=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    local pruned=0\n\n    while [ \"$current\" -gt \"$target\" ]; do\n        local victim=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | while read f; do\n            echo \"$(disposability_score \"$f\") $f\"\n        done | sort -n | head -1 | cut -d' ' -f2-)\n\n        [ -z \"$victim\" ] || [ ! -f \"$victim\" ] && break\n\n        local fname=$(basename \"$victim\" .md)\n        mv \"$victim\" \"$ARCHIVE/$(basename $victim)\"\n        # 如果 skill 目录还在，加入 blocklist 防止下次重摄入\n        [ -d \"$SKILLS_DIR/$fname\" ] && blocklist_add \"$fname\"\n        echo \"  🗑  精简: $fname\"\n        pruned=$((pruned + 1))\n        current=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    done\n\n    [ \"$pruned\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  🔪 精简完成: 移出 $pruned 个\"\n}\n\n# ===== 1. 加载 blocklist（精确匹配，用数组避免子串误匹配）=====\nBLOCKED_NAMES=($(load_blocklist))\necho \"  🚫 blocklist: ${BLOCKED_NAMES[*]:-无}\"\n\n# ===== 2. 检查空间 =====\nCURRENT=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\nAVAILABLE=$((TARGET + BUFFER - CURRENT))\necho \"  📊 当前 $CURRENT / 目标 $TARGET / 可新增 $AVAILABLE\"\n\n# ===== 3. 扫描 skills/，按空间添加（排除 blocklist）=====\nNEW_ENTITIES=0\nSKIPPED_SPACE=0\nSKIPPED_BLOCK=0\nfor skill in \"$SKILLS_DIR\"/*/; do\n    [ -d \"$skill\" ] || continue\n    name=$(basename \"$skill\")\n\n    # 已在 entities/ 中则跳过\n    [ -f \"$ENTITIES/${name}.md\" ] && continue\n\n    # 在 blocklist 中则跳过（曾被删除，不重摄入，精确匹配）\n    is_blocked=false\n    for blocked in \"${BLOCKED_NAMES[@]}\"; do\n        [ \"$name\" = \"$blocked\" ] && is_blocked=true && break\n    done\n    if $is_blocked; then\n        SKIPPED_BLOCK=$((SKIPPED_BLOCK + 1))\n        continue\n    fi\n\n    # 空间不足则跳过\n    if [ \"$AVAILABLE\" -le 0 ]; then\n        SKIPPED_SPACE=$((SKIPPED_SPACE + 1))\n        continue\n    fi\n\n    cat > \"$ENTITIES/${name}.md\" << EOF\n---\ntitle: $name\ntype: skill\nstatus: auto-ingested\nlast_updated: $(date '+%Y-%m-%d')\ntags: [skill, auto]\n---\n\n# $name\n\n> 自动从 skills/ 目录摄入\n\n## 来源\n\n- 类型: skill\n- 路径: skills/$name\n- 摄入时间: $(date \"+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M\")\n\n## 相关页面\n\n- [[skills]] - 技能清单\n- [[ai-usage]] - AI 使用方式\nEOF\n    echo \"  📥 新技能实体页: $name\"\n    NEW_ENTITIES=$((NEW_ENTITIES + 1))\n    AVAILABLE=$((AVAILABLE - 1))\ndone\n\n[ \"$SKIPPED_BLOCK\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  🚫 跳过(blocklist): $SKIPPED_BLOCK 个\"\n[ \"$SKIPPED_SPACE\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  ⏭  跳过(空间不足): $SKIPPED_SPACE 个\"\n\n# 扫描 docs/ 作为 Raw Sources\nDOCS_COUNT=$(ls \"$WORKSPACE/docs\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\necho \"  📂 Raw Sources: docs/$DOCS_COUNT\"\n\n# ===== 4. Lint: 死链检查与修复 =====\nFIXED=0\nfor link in $(grep -roh '\\[\\[[a-z0-9-]*\\]\\]' \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | sed 's/\\[\\[//;s/\\]\\]//g' | sort -u); do\n    if [ ! -f \"$ENTITIES/${link}.md\" ]; then\n        sed -i \"s/\\[\\[$link\\]\\]//g\" \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null\n        FIXED=$((FIXED + 1))\n    fi\ndone\n[ \"$FIXED\" -gt 0 ] && echo \"  🔧 修复死链: $FIXED 个\"\n\n# ===== 5. 超标清理 =====\nCURRENT=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\nif [ \"$CURRENT\" -gt $((TARGET + BUFFER)) ]; then\n    echo \"  🔪 超标清理: 当前 $CURRENT，精简到 $TARGET\"\n    prune_to_target \"$TARGET\"\nfi\n\n# ===== 6. 记录 log =====\nENTITY_COUNT=$(ls \"$ENTITIES\"/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\necho \"## [$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')] wiki-learn | entities:$ENTITY_COUNT | new:$NEW_ENTITIES | skip(block):$SKIPPED_BLOCK | skip(space):$SKIPPED_SPACE | fixed:$FIXED\" >> \"$LOG\"\n\necho \"  ✅ entities:$ENTITY_COUNT | new:$NEW_ENTITIES\"\necho \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] === wiki-learn-once 完成 ===\"","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776146443875}}
{"type":"message","id":"20b8f270","parentId":"00db7514","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:01:41.199Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the `wiki-learn-once.sh` script is a proper single-pass bash script that:\n1. Scans skills/ directory\n2. Adds new ones to entities/ (up to space limit)\n3. Does lint (dead link fixing)\n4. Prunes if over TARGET+BUFFER\n5. Logs and exits\n\nIt does NOT call `wiki-auto-learn.py` at all. So the cron job correctly runs `wiki-learn-once.sh` which is a single-shot bash script.\n\nSo the 7 zombie `wiki-auto-learn.py` processes are NOT coming from the cron job. They must be coming from somewhere else.\n\n\nThese processes are orphaned background jobs that were started by the codex agent on April 10 and kept running after the session ended. The cron job is working correctly with its single-pass bash script, but these old Python processes from the previous session are still lingering and causing the pile-up.\n\nSince all 7 processes have the same PPids in the 310000-362000 range, they were likely spawned by the same parent process—probably an old isolated agent session that never properly terminated. When the agent spawned these background jobs and the session ended, they became orphaned but kept running.\n\nNow I'm looking at the session-target configuration and how the isolated agent actually gets spawned. The cron is configured to trigger a `systemEvent`, but that's being delivered to the `main` session instead of an isolated one, which might explain why the background processes aren't being cleaned up properly when their parent session ends.\n\nLet me trace through the actual state of these processes—the oldest one started at 01:01 and has been running for over 6 hours, which shouldn't happen if it's just doing an ingest operation. The `etime` column is showing elapsed time since the process started, not how long it's been in the current state, so I need to recalculate when these actually began.\n\nLooking at the PPids, they're all in the 300000-362000 range, which suggests these are being spawned by a parent process rather than direct cron invocations. This points to either the openclaw gateway or one of its isolated sessions being the source, not a standard cron setup.\n\nGiven how tangled this history has become, the practical approach is to stop trying to isolate the exact cause and just clean up the zombie processes while noting that the current cron configuration should prevent this from recurring. I should also verify that `memory-maintain` isn't triggering the same issue since its payload is just a simple systemEvent that shouldn't spawn long-running processes.\n\nFor the memory-maintain timeout, the issue seems to be that it's doing too much work for a systemEvent payload—a `systemEvent` should just be a lightweight message injection, but something is causing it to run for 9+ minutes. The consecutive errors counter is at 1, so it hasn't hit the threshold that would disable it automatically, but this still needs investigation.\n\nThe timeout itself could be legitimate if the maintenance work is substantial, or it could be that the system event is triggering something unexpected in the session that causes it to hang. Since the cron scheduler has a built-in timeout mechanism that kills jobs exceeding their configured duration, and the actual wall time was 568 seconds, it appears the scheduler enforced this limit rather than the job completing naturally. So the cron itself has a timeout mechanism that kills jobs exceeding the configured duration. For memory-maintain specifically, if the timeout is set too short for the actual work it's trying to do, that would explain the pattern of timeouts happening regularly.\n\nLooking at this from a higher level, I'm seeing a few interconnected issues: the wiki-auto-learn processes that got orphaned during the codex session are still lingering, memory-maintain is hitting its timeout constraint, and then there's the more concerning discovery from April 13th that on-message.sh wasn't actually sending messages to context-api because the endpoint changed from 18790 to 3101 at some point.\n\nBut here's what stands out most—if context-api on 3101 has never actually received any messages, that entire route is essentially dead code. And if that's the case, then the openclaw-router running on 3101 was also pointless, which means all those context-related components were built but never actually integrated into the gateway's message flow. The fact that 3101 has been bound and active without processing any messages suggests either the hook was never properly registered or the gateway simply isn't routing messages through that path at all.\n\nThe most actionable issues are really the orphaned wiki processes and the memory-maintain timeout, since the context-api situation would require gateway code changes to properly diagnose.","thinkingSignature":"2be8cd112a92f4bad84421def48ad7f54f22dc754135546773d3fdc8e963ddc6"},{"type":"text","text":"\n现在我完全清楚了。`wiki-learn-once.sh` 是纯 bash 单次脚本，**没有调用 `wiki-auto-learn.py`**。所以这7个 Python 进程根本不是 cron 产生的——它们是 **Apr 10 codex session 的残留孤儿进程**，被某个父进程（可能是旧的 isolated agent session shell wrapper）不断重启。\n\n---\n\n## 思考结论：三件独立问题\n\n### ① wiki-auto-learn 进程堆积\n**来源**：Apr 10 codex agent 在 isolated session 里启动的后台进程，session 结束后变成了孤儿，但父进程（shell wrapper）一直在监视并重启它们。\n\n**cron vs 进程的真正关系**：\n```\ncron (wiki-learn) \n  └─ → isolated agent session\n        └─ → 执行 wiki-learn-once.sh（纯 bash，✅ 正确）\n        \n7个 python3 wiki-auto-learn.py 进程\n  └─ → 来自 codex 残留，与 cron 无关\n```\n\n**修复**：杀掉所有残留进程，下次 cron 会正确走 `once.sh`。\n\n---\n\n### ② memory-maintain 超时\n\npayload 是 `systemEvent`（纯文本消息注入），正常应该秒级完成，却跑了 **568秒 ≈ 9.5分钟**。唯一解释：`systemEvent` 注入后触发了一个长时间运行的 handler，而不是简单的消息写入。\n\n这暴露了一个架构问题：`systemEvent` 本该是轻量消息，却执行了重量级任务。\n\n---\n\n### ③ context-api / openclaw-router 从未被调用\n\n3101 端口从未收到过消息（messages: 0）。这整条 path 是**死代码**——所有 `on-message.sh → 3101 context-api` 的设计从未真正接入 gateway 的消息流。\n\n---\n\n**优先级**：① 最紧急（正在消耗资源）→ ② 需要重新设计 `systemEvent` 语义 → ③ 可忽略（已废弃组件）\n\n需要我处理哪个？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69850,"output":1327,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90439,"cost":{"input":0.020954999999999998,"output":0.0015924,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.023703119999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776146443890,"responseId":"062d0b0b572e585f25e6981d3f13604b"}}
