{"type":"message","id":"b4d81e78","parentId":"8ac63c51","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:09:21.986Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The payload is just a systemEvent text message: \"每日记忆系统维护脚本已运行\" (6 characters). And the duration was 568760ms (~9.5 minutes).\n\nWhen a `systemEvent` is delivered to the main session with `sessionTarget: \"main\"`, what happens? The text is injected as a system message into the session. This should be processed immediately.\n\nBut 9.5 minutes is very long. The `lastError` says \"cron: job execution timed out\" - this is the cron system's own timeout, not the task itself.\n\nWait - `sessionTarget: \"main\"` with `payload.kind: \"systemEvent\"` - when the cron fires, does it inject the text into the main agent session? If so, the main agent would receive this as a message and try to respond. If the agent's response takes >9 minutes, the cron would time out.\n \nSo \"每日记忆系统维护脚本已运行\" is actually a prompt that triggers the memory maintenance script, not just a notification. The agent interprets this and executes a script that handles the maintenance work, which is why it takes so long. The cron system just sends the text and waits for the agent to complete the task.\n\nBut here's the problem: if the agent is in the middle of processing another request when this system event fires, it either queues the message or gets confused about context. That's likely why it's timing out. The better approach would be to run the maintenance script directly as an isolated agent session instead of trying to inject it as a message into the main session. Alternatively, I could just remove the memory-maintain cron job since the agent does maintenance automatically during heartbeats. Let me focus on fixing the immediate issue.\n\nThe timeout happens because systemEvent is a message that triggers an agent response, not a direct script execution. The 568-second duration suggests the maintenance script runs for about 9.5 minutes before timing out. The solution is to change the cron job to run the script directly in an isolated session rather than sending it to the main agent. I also need to verify whether the memory-keeper cron job has the same problem.","thinkingSignature":"4f61272e80acd11e1d6a1256007420ec99181402d69d7647ff5659aa717ec9de"},{"type":"text","text":"**发现根因：** `payload.kind: \"systemEvent\"` 是向主 session 注入一条文本消息，而不是执行脚本。文本内容是\"每日记忆系统维护脚本已运行\"——agent 收到后会启动维护逻辑，但主 session 若正忙就会堆积直到超时（9.5分钟）。\n\n对比 `memory-keeper`（同类 `systemEvent`，耗时仅 6ms）→ 说明 agent 正确处理了简单消息。`memory-maintain` 超时说明维护任务本身很重，在9分钟内未完成。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kgsdumdwpd7y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 查看 memory-keeper 的 payload，看它为什么只跑6ms\ncat /home/ai/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor j in data['jobs']:\n    if j['name'] == 'memory-keeper':\n        print(json.dumps(j, indent=2))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49997,"output":647,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69906,"cost":{"input":0.0149991,"output":0.0007764,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.016931219999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776146936358,"responseId":"062d0cf87a53cccd9490e3743a9a00b2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c269ef2","parentId":"b4d81e78","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:09:22.133Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kgsdumdwpd7y_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"e3ff05f4-6d75-4c58-8f4c-d4de23b82ab1\",\n  \"agentId\": \"main\",\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n  \"name\": \"memory-keeper\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1775278283916,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1776110400010,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"expr\": \"0 4 * * *\",\n    \"tz\": \"Asia/Shanghai\",\n    \"kind\": \"cron\"\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"main\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"systemEvent\",\n    \"text\": \"Memory Keeper \\u6574\\u7406\\u4efb\\u52a1\\u5df2\\u6267\\u884c\"\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"none\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1776196800000,\n    \"lastRunAtMs\": 1776110400004,\n    \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n    \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n    \"lastDurationMs\": 6,\n    \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-requested\",\n    \"consecutiveErrors\": 0\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":83,"aggregated":"{\n  \"id\": \"e3ff05f4-6d75-4c58-8f4c-d4de23b82ab1\",\n  \"agentId\": \"main\",\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n  \"name\": \"memory-keeper\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1775278283916,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1776110400010,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"expr\": \"0 4 * * *\",\n    \"tz\": \"Asia/Shanghai\",\n    \"kind\": \"cron\"\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"main\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"systemEvent\",\n    \"text\": \"Memory Keeper \\u6574\\u7406\\u4efb\\u52a1\\u5df2\\u6267\\u884c\"\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"none\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1776196800000,\n    \"lastRunAtMs\": 1776110400004,\n    \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n    \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n    \"lastDurationMs\": 6,\n    \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-requested\",\n    \"consecutiveErrors\": 0\n  }\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776146962117}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f67c3bb","parentId":"1c269ef2","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:09:43.068Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both `memory-maintain` and `memory-keeper` are `systemEvent` to `sessionTarget: \"main\"`. The `memory-keeper` only takes 6ms because its message \"Memory Keeper 整理任务已执行\" is just a notification - the agent processes it and returns immediately (probably with `HEARTBEAT_OK` or a brief acknowledgment).\n\nBut `memory-maintain` with message \"每日记忆系统维护脚本已运行\" causes a 9.5 minute timeout. Why?\n\nThe difference is the message content:\n- `memory-keeper`: \"Memory Keeper 整理任务已执行\" - a passive notification, agent probably replies \"好的\" or similar\n\n\n- `memory-maintain`: \"每日记忆系统维护脚本已运行\" - this is a prompt/instruction to run the maintenance script, so the agent interprets it as a command to execute the actual maintenance work rather than just acknowledge it\n\nSo the agent tries to do actual work instead of just replying. And if that work takes more than 9.5 minutes, it times out.\n\nThe real issue is that these `systemEvent` messages are supposed to be low-latency notifications, but \"每日记忆系统维护脚本已运行\" is phrased as an instruction that triggers heavy processing. I could either rephrase it to be passive like the keeper's message, or switch to a different delivery mechanism like `agentTurn` that supports longer-running tasks. The challenge is that `systemEvent` to the main session doesn't seem to be the right approach for triggering actual work that takes minutes to complete. The core issue is that a `systemEvent` to the main session can trigger agent processing that doesn't complete within the timeout window. I need to either convert this to an `agentTurn` in an isolated session with a proper timeout, or increase the cron timeout threshold since 568 seconds suggests the maintenance task itself takes around 9.5 minutes. Let me check what the actual maintenance script does to understand the timing better.","thinkingSignature":"d51bf9ff52d5bb72c35cae7b135170c7990baf83075af06433af360b2224f8f2"},{"type":"text","text":"**关键差异：** `memory-keeper` (6ms) vs `memory-maintain` (568s)。消息内容不同导致 agent 行为不同：\n- keeper: \"已执行\" → 被动通知，agent 秒回\n- maintain: \"已运行\" → 被理解为指令，agent 尝试执行维护脚本，9.5分钟未完成\n\n**修复方案：** 将 `systemEvent` 改为直接执行脚本，用 `agentTurn` isolated session，配置足够长的 timeout。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ojzm4hv1khr7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 找到维护脚本的实际路径\nls /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/*.sh 2>/dev/null | xargs -I{} basename {}\necho \"---\"\nls /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/*.py 2>/dev/null | xargs -I{} basename {}"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50946,"output":596,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70804,"cost":{"input":0.0152838,"output":0.0007151999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01715472}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776146962134,"responseId":"062d0d120a97ffa21610a2edfb3f1527"}}
