{"type":"message","id":"a33db47c","parentId":"f37c8c2a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:11:06.543Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tmi0blpk0n8n_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# OpenClaw Context Hook - HTTP 版本\n# 将消息发送到保护层的 HTTP 服务\n\nMESSAGE=\"${OPENCLAW_MESSAGE:-}\"\nUSER=\"${OPENCLAW_SENDER:-unknown}\"\nCHANNEL=\"${OPENCLAW_CHANNEL:-unknown}\"\nSERVER_URL=\"http://127.0.0.1:3101\"\n\nif [ -n \"$MESSAGE\" ]; then\n  # 发送到 Context API（openclaw-router）\n  curl -s -X POST \"${SERVER_URL}/api/context\" \\\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n    -d \"{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"$(echo \"$MESSAGE\" | jq -Rs .)\\\",\\\"user\\\":\\\"$USER\\\",\\\"channel\\\":\\\"$CHANNEL\\\"}\" \\\n    > /dev/null 2>&1 || true\nfi"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":99,"aggregated":"#!/bin/bash\n# OpenClaw Context Hook - HTTP 版本\n# 将消息发送到保护层的 HTTP 服务\n\nMESSAGE=\"${OPENCLAW_MESSAGE:-}\"\nUSER=\"${OPENCLAW_SENDER:-unknown}\"\nCHANNEL=\"${OPENCLAW_CHANNEL:-unknown}\"\nSERVER_URL=\"http://127.0.0.1:3101\"\n\nif [ -n \"$MESSAGE\" ]; then\n  # 发送到 Context API（openclaw-router）\n  curl -s -X POST \"${SERVER_URL}/api/context\" \\\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n    -d \"{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"$(echo \"$MESSAGE\" | jq -Rs .)\\\",\\\"user\\\":\\\"$USER\\\",\\\"channel\\\":\\\"$CHANNEL\\\"}\" \\\n    > /dev/null 2>&1 || true\nfi","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776147066533}}
{"type":"message","id":"c5552635","parentId":"a33db47c","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:11:23.399Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting. The `on-message.sh` is a shell script that:\n1. Reads `OPENCLAW_MESSAGE`, `OPENCLAW_SENDER`, `OPENCLAW_CHANNEL` environment variables\n2. POSTs to `http://127.0.0.1:3101/api/context`\n\nBut the context-api process (pid 88283) is NOT listening on 3101. Wait, the pid 88283 is the Scene Classifier on port 3105! Let me re-read.\n\nActually: `ps aux` showed:\n```\nai 88283 ... /usr/bin/python3 api_server.py\n```\n\nBut earlier I saw that 3105 is listening with `pt_main_thread`. Hmm, that's the Scene Classifier. So who is pid 88283? The Scene Classifier showed `pt_main_thread` on 3105.\n\n\nLet me verify this. The python3 api_server.py at pid 88283 doesn't seem to be bound to 3101 based on the ss output, so it might be something else entirely. Looking back at the scene-classifier directory, it has a Python-based classifier, but the process list shows `/usr/bin/python3 api_server.py` rather than something explicitly tied to that classifier.\n\nActually, wait—the ps output doesn't show a command line for that process, just the binary path. It could be an older Python process that's unrelated to the scene-classifier. I should check the actual command line for pid 88283 to confirm what it's running, and then figure out why port 3101 isn't being used by the context-api when it seems like it should be.","thinkingSignature":"b9904a3fe6c4e83c518013bd235c6cf2451b333426e69e2b47d510764dc9cd7c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q7n3yteoab7h_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 pid 88283 到底是什么\necho \"=== pid 88283 详情 ===\"\ncat /proc/88283/cmdline 2>/dev/null | tr '\\0' ' '\necho \"\"\ncat /proc/88283/environ 2>/dev/null | tr '\\0' '\\n' | grep -E \"PORT|SERVER|HOST\" | head -5\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 所有 python3 进程 ===\"\nps aux | grep python3 | grep -v grep | grep -v snap"}},{"type":"toolCa