{"type":"message","id":"ceedc5c7","parentId":"46a1afaf","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:11:58.090Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now it's clear! The context-api (pid 88283, python3) is actually the **scene-classifier** service. It uses PORT=3106 according to its `.env`, but the `.env` says `PORT=3106`. And it IS listening on 3105 (as `pt_main_thread`), not 3101 or 3106. This is confusing.\n\nWait - let me re-examine. The `.env` in `/home/ai/.openclaw/context-api/.env` has `PORT=3106`. But the scene-classifier's `api_server.py` is in `/home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/`. These are two different directories.\n \nSo the context-api at pid 88283 is actually the scene-classifier service from `/home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/`, and it's listening on 3105 as `pt_main_thread`. That would explain why the ss output shows 3105 with `pt_main_thread` instead of the node process I expected.\n\nThe real question is whether 3101 is actually dead code—on-message.sh is trying to POST to 127.0.0.1:3101, but nothing's listening there. So on-message.sh just fails silently when it can't connect. The question is whether on-message.sh itself is even being triggered in the first place.","thinkingSignature":"8361e10c97ddabebff3ca08803b79b5295d4dbf93e36c86ec4a37a273e76de3a"},{"type":"text","text":"**确认：** pid 88283 是 scene-classifier（`/home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/`），它监听 3105。**3101 端口完全无监听服务**。context-api 是旧废弃组件。\n\n现在检查 gateway 的 hook 配置，看 `on-message.sh` 是否真的会被 gateway 调用：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7hf3cjk95eaw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 查看 gateway 的 hook 配置\ncat /home/ai/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | grep -A 20 '\"hooks\"'"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7hf3cjk95eaw_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 HOOK.md 中关于 message hook 的说明\ncat /home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/HOOK.md 2>/dev/null | grep -A 10 -i \"message\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages