{"type":"message","id":"f9d74e96","parentId":"ce85f46d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:14:00.475Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to think comprehensively about whether everything is truly fixed and the system is fully functional. Let me do a deep critical review.\n\nLet me think about what we've done and what could still be wrong:\n\n1. ✅ Killed wiki-auto-learn processes - but this was a temporary fix. The root cause was isolated sessions spawning the python process. We didn't change any code to prevent this from happening again. The next time an isolated session starts a background python process, it could happen again.\n\n2. ✅ memory-maintain text changed - but the real issue is that systemEvent → main session is fundamentally wrong design. \n\nChanging the text to a passive notification might work for a while, but if there's a deeper issue with how systemEvent triggers maintenance logic, the agent could still get stuck again.\n\n3. ⚠️ The classification null issue from Apr 13 session - we never actually verified this is fixed. The context.json from the Apr 13 session showed `classification: null` even though 3105 API works fine. We never confirmed whether this was fixed in subsequent runs.\n\n4. ⚠️ The bootstrap/session-summary chain - the Apr 13 review mentioned this was \"never truly verified\". We still don't know if bootstrap actually works.\n\n5. ⚠️ ephemeral data flow - we never verified ephemeral is actually capturing and flowing into session-summary properly.\n\n6. Let me check the current state of these things to see if they're still problematic.","thinkingSignature":"b06dfb6a7de5450c10eae6915bd026315c853ede476675faad8626243ce55269"},{"type":"text","text":"让我彻底想一遍，不是表面检查，而是追根溯源。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r7wqpwqkj8lv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 深度检查1: ephemeral 是否真的在工作\necho \"=== ephemeral 最近写入 ===\"\nls -lt /home/ai/.openclaw/memory/ephemeral/ 2>/dev/null | head -10