{"type":"message","id":"e942a0bb","parentId":"1f345f27","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:15:01.400Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! Now I see that:\n\n1. **ephemeral IS working** - there are hourly jsonl files, the latest is `2026-04-14-06.jsonl` (updated at 14:01). The directory was empty because I was looking at the wrong path - I was looking at `/home/ai/.openclaw/memory/ephemeral/` instead of `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/`.\n\n2. The hook fires on `event.type === \"message\"` AND `event.action === \"preprocessed\"`. Both conditions must be met.\n\nNow let me check the session-summary issue. The session-summary hook fires on what event? And does it actually work? We saw there's only one session-summary file: `2026-04-13-session-summary.md`. \n\nLooking at the auto-score-classify handler more closely, it captures meaningful messages and writes them to ephemeral storage with a timestamp, session key, the full text, a truncated preview, and both classification and scoring data - so ephemeral is definitely capturing meaningful events. The gateway hasn't generated a new session-summary since April 13th, even though ephemeral files are being written every hour. I need to figure out what event triggers the session-summary hook and why it hasn't fired since that date, plus verify the bootstrap mechanism is functioning properly.","thinkingSignature":"92849e9649b008a9c34a92d88fab676823f84107f08de1eb682293da56ca598c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_phxitrdztfag_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# session-summary hook 触发条件\ngrep -A 10 \"export default\\|function handler\\|event.type\\|session.*end\\|session.*close\" \\\n  /home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js | head -40"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_phxitrdztfag_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 bootstrap hook 的实际注入逻辑（handler.js 里应该有）\ngrep -A 30 \"session-summary\\|bootstrap\\|agent:bootstrap\" \\\n  /home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60607,"output":418,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80287,"cost":{"input":0.0181821,"output":0.0005015999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01983942}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776147287312,"responseId":"062d0e56597ba92c89ce5c26faf5e7a9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6deba422","parentId":"e942a0bb","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:15:01.550Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_phxitrdztfag_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":".filter(n => n.startsWith(`${sessionId.trim()}-topic-`) && n.endsWith('.jsonl') && !n.includes('.reset.'))\n        .sort()\n        .reverse()[0];\n      if (topicVariant) return path.join(sessionsDir, topicVariant);\n    }\n    // 4. fallback: 最新 .jsonl\n    if (!currentSessionFile) {\n      const latest = files\n        .filter(n => n.endsWith('.jsonl') && !n.includes('.reset.'))\n        .sort()\n        .reverse()[0];\n--\n  const isTarget = event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\");\n  if (!isTarget) return;\n\n  const now = new Date();\n  const date = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[0];\n  const time = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[1].split(\".\")[0].slice(0, 5);\n\n  // 1. 解析 session 文件路径（搜索 sessions/ 目录作为兜底）\n  const workspaceDir = event.context?.workspaceDir ||\n    (event.context?.cfg ? path.join(os.homedir(), '.openclaw', 'workspace') : null);\n  const sessionFile = await resolveSessionFile(event.context || {}, workspaceDir);\n--\nexport default function handler(event) {\n  run(event).catch((err) => {\n    console.error(\"[session-summary] Uncaught error:\", err);\n  });\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":90,"aggregated":".filter(n => n.startsWith(`${sessionId.trim()}-topic-`) && n.endsWith('.jsonl') && !n.includes('.reset.'))\n        .sort()\n        .reverse()[0];\n      if (topicVariant) return path.join(sessionsDir, topicVariant);\n    }\n    // 4. fallback: 最新 .jsonl\n    if (!currentSessionFile) {\n      const latest = files\n        .filter(n => n.endsWith('.jsonl') && !n.includes('.reset.'))\n        .sort()\n        .reverse()[0];\n--\n  const isTarget = event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\");\n  if (!isTarget) return;\n\n  const now = new Date();\n  const date = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[0];\n  const time = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[1].split(\".\")[0].slice(0, 5);\n\n  // 1. 解析 session 文件路径（搜索 sessions/ 目录作为兜底）\n  const workspaceDir = event.context?.workspaceDir ||\n    (event.context?.cfg ? path.join(os.homedir(), '.openclaw', 'workspace') : null);\n  const sessionFile = await resolveSessionFile(event.context || {}, workspaceDir);\n--\nexport default function handler(event) {\n  run(event).catch((err) => {\n    console.error(\"[session-summary] Uncaught error:\", err);\n  });\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776147301542}}
{"type":"message","id":"3f36ba83","parentId":"6deba422","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:15:01.570Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_phxitrdztfag_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"* 1. Self-Improvement reminder during agent bootstrap\n * 2. Previous session's summary (memory/*-session-summary.md) as bootstrap context\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport os from 'node:os';\n\nconst SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER = `## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.`;\n\n/**\n * Find and read the most recent session-summary file.\n * Looks in memory/ for *-session-summary.md files, returns most recent by mtime.\n */\nasync function getLatestSessionSummary() {\n  try {\n    const memoryDir = path.join(\n      process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(os.homedir(), '.openclaw', 'workspace'),\n      'memory'\n    );\n\n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(memoryDir);\n    const summaryFiles = files.filter(f => f.endsWith('-session-summary.md'));\n\n    if (summaryFiles.length === 0) return null;\n\n    // Sort by mtime descending\n    const withMtime = await Promise.all(\n      summaryFiles.map(async (f) => ({\n        file: f,\n        mtime: (await fs.promises.stat(path.join(memoryDir, f))).mtimeMs,\n      }))\n    );\n    withMtime.sort((a, b) => b.mtime - a.mtime);\n\n    const latest = withMtime[0].file;\n    const content = await fs.promises.readFile(path.join(memoryDir, latest), 'utf-8');\n\n    // Strip <!-- summary-only --> and <!-- source: ... --> tags for clean injection\n    const cleaned = content\n      .replace(/<!-- summary-only -->/g, '')\n      .replace(/<!-- source:[^>]*>/g, '')"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":109,"aggregated":"* 1. Self-Improvement reminder during agent bootstrap\n * 2. Previous session's summary (memory/*-session-summary.md) as bootstrap context\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport os from 'node:os';\n\nconst SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER = `## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.`;\n\n/**\n * Find and read the most recent session-summary file.\n * Looks in memory/ for *-session-summary.md files, returns most recent by mtime.\n */\nasync function getLatestSessionSummary() {\n  try {\n    const memoryDir = path.join(\n      process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(os.homedir(), '.openclaw', 'workspace'),\n      'memory'\n    );\n\n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(memoryDir);\n    const summaryFiles = files.filter(f => f.endsWith('-session-summary.md'));\n\n    if (summaryFiles.length === 0) return null;\n\n    // Sort by mtime descending\n    const withMtime = await Promise.all(\n      summaryFiles.map(async (f) => ({\n        file: f,\n        mtime: (await fs.promises.stat(path.join(memoryDir, f))).mtimeMs,\n      }))\n    );\n    withMtime.sort((a, b) => b.mtime - a.mtime);\n\n    const latest = withMtime[0].file;\n    const content = await fs.promises.readFile(path.join(memoryDir, latest), 'utf-8');\n\n    // Strip <!-- summary-only --> and <!-- source: ... --> tags for clean injection\n    const cleaned = content\n      .replace(/<!-- summary-only -->/g, '')\n      .replace(/<!-- source:[^>]*>/g, '')","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776147301562}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ace54e1","parentId":"3f36ba83","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:15:12.632Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the key findings:\n\n1. **session-summary hook** fires on `event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\")`. This is when the user runs `/new` or `/reset`. So it requires a `/new` command to trigger. If no one has run `/new` since Apr 13, no new summary would be generated.\n\n2. **bootstrap hook (handler.js)** fires on `agent:bootstrap` event, reads the most recent `*-session-summary.md` and injects it. But if no `/new` was run (so no new summary generated), the bootstrap would inject the old Apr 13 summary.\n   \n3. **ephemeral is working correctly** - hourly files are being written as expected.\n\nI should check when the last `/new` command actually ran to understand why there's no newer summary.","thinkingSignature":"d1867e63aae9435fccac29d4afbbd88d41c14f513dfec6ce3741f2dc3039972b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2x9m8qpn5mfv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 查看 gateway 日志里 /new 的触发记录\ntail -100 /home/ai/.openclaw/logs/gateway.log 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"/new|reset|newSession|agent:bootstrap\" | tail -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2x9m8qpn5mfv_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 Apr 14 是否有新的 session-summary 生成\nls -la /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/*-session-summary* 2>/dev/null\n\necho \"\"\n# 检查 Apr 13 session-summary 的内容（最新那个）\ncat /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-13-session-summary.md 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":61892,"output":360,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81514,"cost":{"input":0.0185676,"output":0.000432,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.020155319999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776147301572,"responseId":"062d0e65ddddc10472490e739f3b35b2"}}
