{"type":"message","id":"9424be92","parentId":"4fe25e9f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:15:47.395Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! Key finding from context.json:\n\n1. **classification is working** - `scene: \"clarify\"`, confidence: 0.775 - it's not null anymore! The Apr 14 14:13 message (\"思考一下，都好了吗？\") was processed and got a valid classification.\n\n2. **scoring is working** - score: 0, recommendedStrategy: \"DIRECT\"\n\nSo the classification null issue from Apr 13 appears to be **fixed**. The hook is correctly calling 3105 and getting valid responses.\n\nNow let me check the broader picture:\n\n**Still concerning:**\n1. gateway.log is from Apr 13 - no new logs being written. Where are the current logs going?\n\n\n2. The ephemeral hourly files show activity through Apr 14 06:00, and we processed the 14:13 message with valid results, but I'm wondering if messages in this webchat session actually trigger the auto-score-classify hook or if there's a different flow for webhook/messages that bypasses it entirely.","thinkingSignature":"bc7c4082a680dc3bb47319e20c59a3f7528032e784ce1963cca2a8893e6a0838"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_myoqmuk81yz9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 gateway 的日志配置 - gateway.log 为什么没更新\ncat /home/ai/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | grep -A 10 \"logging\\|log\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_myoqmuk81yz9_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 sessions 目录结构 - 确认当前 session 的消息历史\nls -la /home/ai/.openclaw/sessions/agent\\:main\\:main/ 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_myoqmuk81yz9_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 ephemeral 最新文件的内容（确认 auto-score-classify 实际写入了 Apr 14 的数据）\ntail -5 /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/2026-04-14-06.jsonl 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    line = line.strip()\n    if line:\n        try:\n            obj = json.