{"type":"message","id":"8922740e","parentId":"fa355fb9","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:16:35.598Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the complete picture. Let me compile a thorough critical review.\n\n**What's working:**\n1. ✅ **3103 scorer** - working correctly, returns valid scores\n2. ✅ **3105 classifier** - working correctly, returns valid scene+confidence\n3. ✅ **Gateway** - running, processing messages\n4. ✅ **ephemeral** - working, hourly files with valid classification data\n5. ✅ **auto-score-classify hook** - working, writes to context.json with valid classification\n6. ✅ **cron jobs** - all registered and mostly healthy (memory-maintain error was from old text)\n\n\n7. ✅ **Entities** - stable at 41 with maintenance scripts running correctly\n8. ✅ **Wiki-learn cron** - operational and functional\n\n**What I still don't know for certain:**\n1. The **bootstrap chain** (ephemeral → session-summary → bootstrap inject) hasn't been fully verified since no /new command was issued today to trigger it\n2. The **memory-maintain text change** was applied but won't be tested until tonight at 3 AM\n3. Whether the **context Hook** (global.openclaw.addContextMessage) is actually functioning or just a no-op\n4. The **classification null** issue appears resolved based on current context, though it was problematic on Apr 13\n5. The **gateway logging level** is set to \"warn\" so most events aren't being recorded\n\nThe Apr 14 06:13 context shows the auto-score-classify hook is actively running and updating context.json with valid classification data, so that null issue seems to have been resolved. However, I'm noticing something odd: the context.json captures one message at 06:13 but the ephemeral file only has entries up to 06:01, which doesn't align.\n\nWait, I'm confusing the session state. The webchat session I'm in right now (agent=main) only has context.json with my 14:13 message, meaning no history file exists in the session directory. The ephemeral files are tied to different sessions, so they're tracking different message flows than what I'm seeing in the current context.\n\nNow I'm realizing the core issue: when I said \"思考一下，都好了吗？\" the auto-score-classify hook actually ran and produced a valid classification (scene: clarify), but this result only got written to context.json—it didn't also write to ephemeral the way I'd expect. Let me trace through why that might be.\n\nThe hook seems to be firing correctly since the context shows classification data, but it's not persisting to ephemeral storage. I'm also noticing that session-summary isn't generating new summaries without a /new command, which is expected but worth tracking. The memory-maintain fix won't be validated until tonight at 3 AM, and there's a potential issue with how HOOK.md references memory-bootstrap as a directory when it might not exist.","thinkingSignature":"47d20002bf1943e551671ab5489b4fc5fbcb0f68dce86ec35cacdb1597d346ad"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uqlhacbrnifo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 self-improvement hook（处理 bootstrap）\ncat /home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/self-improvement.js 2>/dev/null | head -30"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uqlhacbrnifo_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 确认 HOOK.md 里的 bootstrap 配置\ncat /home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/HOOK.md 2>/dev/null | grep -B2 -A 15 \"memory-bootstrap\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65117,"output":697,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85076,"cost":{"input":0.0195351,"output":0.0008364,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02152722}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776147366399,"responseId":"062d0ea6ea5789575606068258a75ff2"}}
