{"type":"message","id":"a942b296","parentId":"b8d63be8","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:49:03.713Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `characters_facts.yaml` doesn't have `---` separators. But `林枫.yaml` character file does. The `loadFacts()` in `generate-chapter.js` uses `yaml.load()` directly on the facts files, which should work since they don't have multiple documents.\n\nThe main bugs are:\n1. Character files in `characters/` that are multi-document YAML\n2. `青云子.yaml` which isn't valid YAML at all\n\nNow let me look at what the `generate-chapter.js` does exactly when it fails. Let me trace the error more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"e414a823473e926ecdbcca475a543e66eaf06cbda63b5daa09b13977b2a353be"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_osvrh3c4cljk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/my-novel-tools/bin/generate-chapter.js | grep -n \"expected a single\\|yaml.load\\|catch\\|error\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98346,"output":183,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117791,"cost":{"input":0.0295038,"output":0.0002196,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03087912}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776149336862,"responseId":"062d1658992787e8eac2d83a73624045"}}
