{"type":"message","id":"85de5665","parentId":"2b61e76e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:54:22.905Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The regex `^\\*\\*(.+?)\\*\\*:\\s*(.+)$` is NOT matching `**姓名**: 青云子`. Let me trace why.\n\nThe regex breakdown:\n- `^` - start of line\n- `\\*` - literal `*`\n- `\\*` - literal `*`\n- `(.+?)` - capture one or more chars (non-greedy)\n- `\\*` - literal `*`\n- `\\*` - literal `*`\n- `:` - literal `:`\n- `\\s*` - zero or more whitespace\n- `(.+)` - capture one or more chars\n\n\n- `$` - end of line\n\nBut wait—the actual line is `**姓名**: 青云子`, which has `**` on both ends with `姓名` in the middle, then `**:` followed by a space and `青云子`. The regex should match this perfectly, so why isn't it working? Let me look at the raw bytes of the actual line to see what's really there.","thinkingSignature":"413324f8df343bf2009bc4676524fca11c95df15154ee96ed74845a7d46c616c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_duofanoge576_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node -e \"\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst content = fs.readFileSync('/mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/my-novel/characters/青云子.yaml', 'utf8');\nconst lines = content.split('\\n');\nconst line4 = lines[3]; // 0-indexed, line 4\nconsole.log('Line 4 JSON:', JSON.stringify(line4));\nconsole.log('Length:', line4.length);\nconsole.log('Char codes:', [...line4].map(c => c.charCodeAt(0)));\n\nconst match = line4.match(/^\\*\\*(.+?)\\*\\*:\\s*(.+)$/);\nconsole.log('Match result:', match ? [match[1], match[2]] : 'NO MATCH');\n\n// Try simpler regex\nconst simple = line4.match(/^\\*\\*(.+?)\\*\\*/);\nconsole.log('Simple match:', simple ? simple[1] : 'NO MATCH');\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":108749,"output":429,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128440,"cost":{"input":0.0326247,"output":0.0005147999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03429522}},"stopReason