{"type":"message","id":"84a018b2","parentId":"3d9fe9b9","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:54:31.192Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is the `\\r` at the end (carriage return, char code 13). The regex `$` doesn't match `\\r` because by default `$` matches the end of the string OR the position before a newline `\\n`, but not before `\\r`. In Windows line endings (`\\r\\n`), `$` only matches before `\\n`, not before `\\r\\n`.\n\nSo the line is `**姓名**: 青云子\\r` and the regex fails because `$` matches the position after `\\n` (which is at position 13), but the actual end of the string is position 12 (the `\\r`).\n\n\nI can fix this by adding `\\r?` to the end of the regex to make it optional, or strip the carriage returns from each line before processing.","thinkingSignature":"f3109b5b646cb42c76c08f2ca85ed9cf21cfaa43c853004385e5f02b4f40a1af"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gbqhqrzflxc0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '50,60p' /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/my-novel-tools/lib/project.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109279,"output":213,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128754,"cost":{"input":0.0327837,"output":0.0002556,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03419502}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776149662484,"responseId":"062d179e1be518282f8a82088ba6f4f8"}}
