{"type":"message","id":"24a7d128","parentId":"1eb2ff20","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:36:54.875Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking \"什么情况\" - they seem confused or want me to explain what's happening. Let me look at what I've been doing and what was interrupted.\n\nLooking at the conversation flow:\n1. The system was providing exec output from a long-running command (build:renderer)\n2. I started doing a systematic review/audit of the tomato-novel-assistant project\n3. I was in the middle of Step 9 (Electron architecture audit), specifically checking the AI IPC handler chain\n4. The user sent \"什么情况\" which means \"what's going on\" or \"what's the situation\"\n\nThe user might be:\n\n\n- Wondering why there's no response (the system events are just exec completion notifications)\n- Confused about what I'm doing\n- Impatient about the review taking so long\n\nLooking at the last meaningful user message: \"按照给出的每一点进行犀利、严格的进行评审、检查\" - they asked me to do a strict review per the points given. Then I ran several exec commands, and before I could deliver the full review findings, the user sent \"什么情况\".\n\nI think they sent \"什么情况\" because I was taking too long between my responses and they got confused about what was happening or what they should do next.\n\nThe last substantive work I did was checking the preload/index.ts file, and I need to continue my audit by looking for the AI IPC handlers in main.ts since the preload exposed ai:saveApiKey, ai:call, ai:stream and other AI methods, but I need to verify these handlers actually exist in main.ts. There's also a potential issue: the preload references `backup:create/list/restore/delete` but I'm not seeing those handlers in main.ts either. Let me wrap up the review findings and give them a clear summary of what I discovered.","thinkingSignature":"cb19ea8d5b7c578ae26fa5e1c922c432de30126b1b3079500a32c671b913a40a"},{"type":"text","text":"我在做严格评审，main/index.ts 里 preload