{"type":"message","id":"23bbac61","parentId":"9f2dfaee","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:39:46.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The files `aiService` and `backupService` don't actually exist as separate files! The `require()` calls in `setupIpcHandlers()` reference modules that don't exist. This means when `startApp()` is called, it will crash at `setupIpcHandlers()` with a \"Cannot find module\" error.\n\nThis is a MAJOR P0 issue - the entire Electron app would crash on startup trying to load non-existent modules!\n\nWait, but the renderer build succeeded. And if `npm run dev:electron` crashes immediately, the user would have noticed. Let me check if maybe there's a tsconfig that handles this differently.\n\nActually wait - the `require()` is in a TypeScript file (`index.ts`). When compiled with `tsc`, it would produce a `.js` file. \n\nThe compiled output would try to `require('./aiService')` which doesn't exist, so this should definitely fail at runtime unless there's some module aliasing or the tsconfig is set up differently than I'm assuming.","thinkingSignature":"1b47e59cf4662b214635279e4a23c34fb7175821c95de8374d81cc8f41897a7d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0yu7e0eph94k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/tsconfig.main.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33438,"output":245,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52945,"cost":{"input":0.0100314,"output":0.000294,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011481119999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776152375439,"responseId":"062d22371a7a778a74555f6cf3711379"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c98d5524","parentId":"23bbac61","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:39:46.965Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0yu7e0eph94k_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2020\",\n    \"module\": \"CommonJS\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"node\",\n    \"outDir\": \"dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"declaration\": false,\n    \"ignoreDeprecations\": \"6.0\"\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/main/**/*\", \"src/preload/**/*\"]\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":85,"aggregated":"{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2020\",\n    \"module\": \"CommonJS\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"node\",\n    \"outDir\": \"dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"declaration\": false,\n    \"ignoreDeprecations\": \"6.0\"\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/main/**/*\", \"src/preload/**/*\"]\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776152386940}}
{"type":"message","id":"17764fdc","parentId":"c98d5524","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:39:58.566Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `tsc -p tsconfig.main.json` would compile `src/main/index.ts` and look for `src/main/aiService.ts`. Since these files don't exist, the compilation should fail or the require would fail at runtime.\n\nBut the user hasn't reported that the Electron app crashes immediately. Let me check if the `npm run dev:electron` was actually successfully run or if it's just \"builds\" (which only builds the renderer with vite, not the electron main process TypeScript).\n\nActually, looking at the package.json scripts:\n- `dev:renderer`: just vite (no tsc for electron)\n\n\n- `dev:electron`: runs `tsc -p tsconfig.main.json && electron .`\n\nSo `npm run dev:electron` would first compile the TypeScript, and if `aiService.ts` doesn't exist, `tsc` would fail before electron even starts. Let me check if there's a dist directory with compiled files that might already exist.","thinkingSignature":"a198ee38b1a83edcf978c4b0e6b33c4e8cc0228422e3fb7174e1433d453ab1ce"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5e0wus0vyld4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/dist/ 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\nls /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/dist/main/ 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# 检查 aiService.ts 是否存在\nls /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/main/aiService.* 2>/dev/null || echo \"aiService 文件不存在\"\nls /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/main/backupService.* 2>/dev/null || echo \"backupService 文件不存在\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33820,"output":336,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53418,"cost":{"input":0.010145999999999999,"output":0.0004032,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011704919999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776152386968,"responseId":"062d2242397c9282fb0dbbaa28222e6f"}}
