{"type":"message","id":"f09b5df3","parentId":"a68c2a5c","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:40:05.461Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very revealing! The `dist/main/index.js` exists, which means `tsc` WAS run successfully. But `aiService.ts` and `backupService.ts` don't exist in `src/main/`. So either:\n\n1. The compilation succeeded despite the missing modules (unlikely - CommonJS require would fail at compile or runtime)\n2. The `dist/main/index.js` is stale from a previous compilation where those modules DID exist\n\nLet me check what the compiled `dist/main/index.js` looks like - does it still have the `require('./aiService')` calls?","thinkingSignature":"07fe1fb5a491bddef0ce115fc9cb8a666ec52250d360d952bdd71fe1e85d1869"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ulauo757kwie_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"aiService\\|backupService\\|setupAi\\|setupBackup\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/dist/main/index.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34193,"output":174,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53629,"cost":{"input":0.0102579,"output":0.00020879999999999998,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011622420000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776152398719,"responseId":"062d224d8216009b65639b51882d9aea"}}
