{"type":"message","id":"ec650385","parentId":"bde83f20","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:59:07.802Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the compiled JS uses `electron_1.ipcMain.handle`. Let me add a YAML-specific IPC handler in `aiService.ts` (which already handles AI IPC) or add a dedicated `yamlService.ts`. Since `aiService.ts` is the most natural place for YAML work (it already handles API keys and settings files), I'll add YAML read/write handlers there.\n\nActually, let me add a `yamlService.ts` to keep things clean. Or better yet, just add it to `aiService.ts` since it's related to file-based config.","thinkingSignature":"ee967171e08563131d730df475eec73860a2d028b1b8313fdb0afff0836b808e"},{"type":"text","text":"**在 aiService.ts 中添加 YAML 读写 IPC：**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_05uhk6fxbj6r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -20 /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/main/aiService.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":59682,"output":172,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79116,"cost":{"input":0.0179046,"output":0.0002064,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.019266719999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776153539271,"responseId":"062d26c29ceee8573066d388a3cac6d5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"232611c9","parentId":"ec650385","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:59:07.917Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_05uhk6fxbj6r_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"})\n\n  // 保存设置\n  ipcMain.handle('ai:saveSetting', async (_event, key: string, value: any) => {\n    try {\n      const settings = loadSettings()\n      settings[key] = value\n      saveSettings(settings)\n      return { success: true }\n    } catch (e: any) {\n      return { success: false, error: e.message }\n    }\n  })\n\n  // 读取设置\n  ipcMain.handle('ai:getSetting', async (_event, key: string, defaultValue?: any) => {\n    const settings = loadSettings()\n    return { success: true, value: settings[key] ?? defaultValue }\n  })\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":71,"aggregated":"})\n\n  // 保存设置\n  ipcMain.handle('ai:saveSetting', async (_event, key: string, value: any) => {\n    try {\n      const settings = loadSettings()\n      settings[key] = value\n      saveSettings(settings)\n      return { success: true }\n    } catch (e: any) {\n      return { success: false, error: e.message }\n    }\n  })\n\n  // 读取设置\n  ipcMain.handle('ai:getSetting', async (_event, key: string, defaultValue?: any) => {\n    const settings = loadSettings()\n    return { success: true, value: settings[key] ?? defaultValue }\n  })\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776153547905}}
{"type":"message","id":"b688c4ff","parentId":"232611c9","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:59:30.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to add two new IPC handlers:\n1. `yaml:read` - read a YAML file and return parsed object\n2. `yaml:write` - serialize object and write to YAML file\n\nThese should be added to `aiService.ts` since it's the file-I/O service layer. And in `factsStore`, instead of using my broken `parseYamlFacts` and hand-rolled `serializeYaml`, I should call these IPC handlers.\n\nBut wait - `aiService.ts` already imports `axios` and handles AI. I should keep it focused. Let me create a separate `yamlService.ts` in main process for YAML operations.","thinkingSignature":"8d11921aacec3718d11a0173d24118f7f8405b070deb21c390e74eaf95f9fc9c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5a9tjw1wkjdb_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/main/yamlService.ts","content":"/**\n * YAML 服务 - 主进程 IPC 处理器\n * 提供 YAML 文件的安全读写，解析和序列化\n */\n\nimport { IpcMain } from 'electron'\nimport fs from 'node:fs'\nimport path from 'node:path'\nimport yaml from 'js-yaml'\n\nexport function setupYamlHandlers(ipcMain: IpcMain): void {\n  // 读取 YAML 文件并返回解析后的对象\n  ipcMain.handle('yaml:read', async (_event, filePath: string): Promise<{ success: boolean; data?: any; error?: string }> => {\n    try {\n      if (!fs.existsSync(filePath)) {\n        return { success: false, error: '文件不存在' }\n      }\n      const content = fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf-8')\n      const data = yaml.load(content)\n      return { success: true, data }\n    } catch (e: any) {\n      return { success: false, error: `YAML 解析失败: ${e.message}` }\n    }\n  })\n\n  // 写入对象序列化为 YAML 文件\n  ipcMain.handle('yaml:write', async (_event, filePath: string, data: any): Promise<{ success: boolean; error?: string }> => {\n    try {\n      const dir = path.dirname(filePath)\n      if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n        fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true })\n      }\n      const yamlStr = yaml.dump(data, { allowUnicode: true, lineWidth: -1, quotingThreshold: 999 })\n      fs.writeFileSync(filePath, yamlStr, 'utf-8')\n      return { success: true }\n    } catch (e: any) {\n      return { success: false, error: `YAML 写入失败: ${e.message}` }\n    }\n  })\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60011,"output":565,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79838,"cost":{"input":0.0180033,"output":0.000678,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01983702}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776153547919,"responseId":"062d26cb28d9fcbc9d056ffd332231d9"}}
