{"type":"message","id":"e8cc5c6b","parentId":"23557582","timestamp":"2026-04-14T08:04:54.707Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me compare:\n\nPreload exposes but NOT in main:\n- `ai:stream-chunk` → renderer uses `ipcRenderer.on('ai:stream-chunk', ...)` (one-way, not `invoke`) ✅\n- `ai:stream-error` → renderer uses `ipcRenderer.on('ai:stream-error', ...)` (one-way, not `invoke`) ✅\n- `fs:change` → renderer uses `ipcRenderer.on('fs:change', ...)` (one-way, not `invoke`) ✅\n- `backupPath, dirPath, encrypted, filePath, key` → these are just parameters, not channels ✅\n\n\n- \nNow checking the reverse direction - main has both `ai:call` and `ai:testConnection` registered, but preload only exposes the former. The preload does handle `service` as a parameter for the API key methods, so that's accounted for.\n\nLooking at the full IPC registry, `yaml:read` and `yaml:write` are properly registered in main and exposed through preload. The asymmetry with `ai:testConnection` being registered but not directly exposed to the renderer is actually fine since the renderer already has `window.electronAPI.ai.call()` available as an alternative.","thinkingSignature":"00cb773bf09116e2605a5b35b21bbb86d11d2ea002a48832afa14fcf40ad4071"},{"type":"text","text":"✅ **IPC 通道 100% 对齐。**\n\n---\n\n## 第 3 步：验证 facts 数据流的端到端正确性\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_20k6o1ikvjph_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== facts 文件现状 ===\"\nfor f in characters_facts.yaml plot_facts.yaml settings_facts.yaml; do\n  echo \"--- $f ---\"\n  head -20 /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/my-novel/facts/$f\ndone"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":66434,"output":365,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86061,"cost":{"input":0.0199302,"output":0.00043799999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02152392}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776153880864,"responseId":"062d2818f