{"type":"message","id":"8582b641","parentId":"e31fd0a1","timestamp":"2026-04-14T08:06:21.828Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `backup:restore` handler doesn't validate `targetPath` for path traversal. This could allow overwriting arbitrary files if a malicious `targetPath` is provided. However, since this is a desktop app where the UI calls this IPC through user action (selecting a restore destination), it's acceptable for now. Let me add a basic validation though.\n\nActually, let me be pragmatic. The security boundary here is the UI itself (user-initiated action), not a network-facing API. The bigger concern was the `yamlService` which I just fixed.\n\nLet me compile everything and move on.","thinkingSignature":"8bcbbdeaeb6ec82963f3e895eb98ee7e920afaa7109b1d6ee0b92fbbe92db921"},{"type":"text","text":"**补一下 backup:restore 的路径验证：**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8cn4tg5ax7ro_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/main/backupService.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"  ipcMain.handle('backup:restore', async (_event, backupPath: string, targetPath?: string) => {\n    try {\n      if (!fs.existsSync(backupPath)) {\n        return { success: false, error: '备份文件不存在' }\n      }\n      if (!targetPath) {\n        return { success: false, error: '未提供恢复目标路径' }\n      }\n\n      await decompressBackup(backupPath, targetPath)","newText":"  ipcMain.handle('backup:restore', async (_event, backupPath: string, targetPath?: string) => {\n    try {\n      if (!fs.existsSync(backupPath)) {\n        return { success: false, error: '备份文件不存在' }\n      }\n      if (!targetPath) {\n        return { success: false, error: '未提供恢复目标路径' }\n      }\n      // 验证目标路径安全（防止路径遍历）\n      const resolved = path.resolve(targetPath)\n      if (resolved.startsWith('/etc') || resolved.match(/^[A-Z]:\\\\(Windows|Program Files)/i)) {\n        return { success: false, error: '禁止恢复到系统路径' }\n      }\n\n      await decompressBackup(backupPath,