{"type":"message","id":"b3254fab","parentId":"b802300f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T08:12:54.775Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see a critical issue! The `aiModels.ts` calls `window.electronAPI.ai.call(prompt, {...})`. Looking at the preload:\n\n```typescript\ncall: (prompt: string, options?: any) => \n  ipcRenderer.invoke('ai:call', prompt, options),\n```\n\nAnd the main process aiService:\n```typescript\nasync function callAI(\n  prompt: string,\n  options: CallOptions = {}\n): Promise<{ success: boolean; content?: string; reasoning?: string; error?: string }> {\n```\n\nThis looks correct. BUT wait - `window.electronAPI` is only available in the main window context. \n\nSo when `aiModelsService.call()` gets invoked in the renderer process, `window.electronAPI.ai.call()` should exist in the preload exposed API, which means the call should go through the IPC channel to the main process handler. But I'm noticing a mismatch in the argument structure - the renderer is passing `prompt` and an options object separately, while the main process handler expects to receive both as separate parameters.\n\nLooking at the preload code, it extracts the prompt and options from the IPC payload, then passes them individually to `ipcRenderer.invoke('ai:call', prompt, options)`. The main process handler then receives these as two separate arguments, so the structure should actually be correct end-to-end. But I need to trace through the actual implementation to confirm there isn't a subtle mismatch somewhere.\n\nThe real concern is that if `window.electronAPI` isn't defined—say, if the preload script fails to load—then `aiModelsService.call()` would throw a TypeError before ever reaching the IPC layer. This would surface as \"window.electronAPI is not defined\" rather than a silent failure. Though in a properly built Electron app with a correctly configured preload script, this shouldn't be an issue.\n\nLooking at the `aiService.ts` implementation, I see a potential problem: it's missing the `deepseek-chat` model variant. The service only handles `deepseek` and `deepseek-chat` as explicit cases, but if the renderer passes `deepseek-chat` as the model name, it would fail the model check and fall through to the error case.","thinkingSignature":"889b66c9e0ff25cee2fd5c88603d4cc632e18bfdb05c90a6fcd331e8852b547d"},{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## 第 8 步：审查 aiService.ts 的模型覆盖和错误处理\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2cbwukzn2cae_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"deepseek\\|doubao\\|model ===\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/main/aiService.ts | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":77440,"output":528,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97230,"cost":{"input":0.023232,"output":0.0006336,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02502132}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776154347535,"responseId":"062d29ef86ad66b890c36ef9155f2ff1"}}
