{"type":"message","id":"cd256b5c","parentId":"8f8f3642","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:33:50.063Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it. The `catharsis.js` uses `volumeChapters` which defaults to 30 (from the `-v` option). So the output \"每卷30章\" is from the DEFAULT value of the `--volume-chapters` option, not from the actual template. This is a documentation/user expectation issue - the default is 30, but when a user specifies `30` chapters total and doesn't specify `--volume-chapters`, it assumes 30 chapters per volume, which means 1 volume only. But the user might expect 5 volumes × 6 chapters.\n\nThis is actually a UX bug - if you run `catharsis.js 30`, it assumes 30 chapters per volume (which means 1 volume for a \"five-volume\" structure). \n\nThe core problem is that `catharsis.js` doesn't automatically read the volume structure from the template when you just pass a total chapter count, so the default volume-chapters value conflicts with the intended five-volume structure. This could definitely confuse users who expect the tool to infer the volume layout from the template itself.","thinkingSignature":"b59492a1b6214efd159ae529b1c0e8ccc7336c257a74219b19ab275f926c217a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kybixkwk75pt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/my-novel-tools/bin/catharsis.js 30 --volume-chapters 6 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":102085,"output":282,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":121629,"cost":{"input":0.0306255,"output":0.0003384,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03211962}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776159219282,"responseId":"062d3cf2f95bbdf0c481f509ba957aa8"}}
