{"type":"message","id":"af62837c","parentId":"3e0108e4","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:34:55.445Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This confirms the P1 UX bug: `--volume-chapters` defaults to 30, but for a five-volume structure with 30 total chapters, it should be 6. This means users who just run `catharsis.js 30` will get wrong output.\n\nLet me fix this by changing the default to a more sensible value (6 chapters per volume for the default five-volume structure).Actually, looking at the tool more carefully - the user provides total chapters (e.g., 30) and the tool generates a catharsis plan. But the `--volume-chapters` option determines when \"big catharsis points\" occur (every `volumeChapters` chapters). The default of 30 means the first big catharsis would be at chapter 30 (if there are 30 chapters total).","thinkingSignature":"2c0fc41983590f8e5d2fad9b51bfb1287acf53ea7b533ae04b9e00e1b1840cdb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_67h107rn1p4w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '8,12p' /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/my-novel-tools/bin/catharsis.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":104674,"output":215,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124151,"cost":{"input":0.0314022,"output":0.000258,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03281592}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776159286928,"responseId":"062d3d37921da3cc98f3c1958b4df363"}}
