{"type":"message","id":"66f2e9b1","parentId":"a65ffd0b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:44:14.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `result.result` is `boolean | undefined`, and `result.success && result.result` could be `boolean | false` = `boolean | false` which is `boolean | false` = `boolean` but actually `result.success && result.result` when `result.success` is `false` gives `false`, and when `result.success` is `true` and `result.result` is `undefined` gives `undefined`. So the return type is `boolean | false | undefined` which doesn't match `boolean`.\n\nThe fix: `return !!(result.success && result.result)` or just explicitly cast.","thinkingSignature":"1a5617c865058b595f1ad0d8200207f94d8e192854c70a93a815b86b8595f5c6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_clbu8od9e3ld_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/renderer/src/services/aiModels.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"      return result.success && result.result","newText":"      return !!(result.success && result.result)"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":119878,"output":210,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139350,"cost":{"input":0.0359634,"output":0.000252,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03737112}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776159847164,"responseId":"062d3f662351c18a2e42df66b197f7fb"}}
