{"type":"message","id":"f2d80c2b","parentId":"d2ad6d17","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:50:27.011Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The main tsconfig has an issue now - I added `\"composite\": true\"` to tsconfig.main.json, but `\"declaration\": false` is incompatible with `\"composite\": true\"`. When `composite: true`, TypeScript requires declaration emit.Let me fix this by either:1. Setting `\"declaration\": true` when `composite: true`\n2. Or removing `composite: true` from tsconfig.main.json since the reference from the renderer isn't actually needed for the build\n\nOption 2 is cleaner - the `references` in the renderer's tsconfig to the main tsconfig isn't strictly necessary. The main tsconfig is only for the main/preload compilation via `tsc -p tsconfig.main.json`. \n\nI should just remove the `references` field from the renderer's tsconfig since it's pointing to the main process config and causing the conflict.","thinkingSignature":"9fa52d538bb221aceccc907e5cdf1527ac6edbc716f2f844f4b45926595db3fe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0jh3ufmpkfbi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/tsconfig.main.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":123424,"output":221,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":142907,"cost":{"input":0.037027199999999996,"output":0.0002652,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.038448119999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776160218077,"responseId":"062d40d992e298be27304ee728355cfe"}}
