{"type":"message","id":"4168d883","parentId":"3b01d08d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:37:08.596Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The script exited with code 1, but it seems the process exited early. This might be because the `set -euo pipefail` caused the script to exit when the first FAIL happened. Let me check what happened and fix the script. The issue is `set -e` combined with `((PASS++))` where the increment returns exit code 1 when PASS is 0 (because 0 is falsy in bash arithmetic). Let me fix the script.","thinkingSignature":"98aa65292c9b05d92f9e7b4c2cf30944fc757f1709e66eac90f423cb4d648850"},{"type":"text","text":"脚本 `set -e` 在 `((PASS++))` 遇到问题（Bash 中 `((0))` 退出码为 1）。修复：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wok38dfd8azz_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/auto-review.sh","edits":[{"oldText":"set -euo pipefail","newText":"set -uo pipefail"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":123594,"output":201,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143057,"cost":{"input":0.0370782,"output":0.00024119999999999998,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.038475119999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776163020901,"responseId":"062d4bcc083571df9917c6b9b64ed67c"}}
