{"type":"message","id":"0311ea59","parentId":"181acc04","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:37:16.174Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the problem with `((PASS++))` when PASS=0 is that in bash, `((0))` evaluates to false (exit code 1). But `((PASS++))` returns the old value (0), so `((0))` would fail. I should use `((PASS++)) || true` or change to `PASS=$((PASS+1))`. Let me fix the functions.","thinkingSignature":"625799e4f73e8f49977ae0d68a9dedafb6b1ed975534c3f43f09a97439f15ab2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f17ob63s33cx_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/auto-review.sh","edits":[{"oldText":"log() { echo \"[$(date +%H:%M:%S)] $1\"; }\npass() { echo \"  ✅ $1\"; ((PASS++)); }\nfail() { echo \"  ❌ $1\"; ((FAIL++)); }","newText":"log() { echo \"[$(date +%H:%M:%S)] $1\"; }\npass() { echo \"  ✅ $1\"; PASS=$((PASS+1)); }\nfail() { echo \"  ❌ $1\"; FAIL=$((FAIL+1)); }"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":123833,"output":265,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143360,"cost":{"input":0.0371499,"output":0.000318,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03862362}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776163028731,"responseId":"062d4bd42ce1d0830bf14effc66934f5"}}
