{"type":"message","id":"69fc708c","parentId":"fa8f327b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:16:55.440Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the preload is compiled to `dist/preload/index.js` but the main process imports it from `src/preload/index.ts`. The main process uses `require('./preload/index')` but with `rootDir: \"src\"` and `outDir: \"dist\"`, the preload files would be at `dist/preload/index.js`. But the main process source is at `src/main/index.ts`. \n\nLooking at the tsconfig.main.json:\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"rootDir\": \"src\",\n    \"outDir\": \"dist\"\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/main/**/*\", \"src/preload/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\nSo `src/main/index.ts` → `dist/main/index.js` ✓\nAnd `src/preload/index.ts` → `dist/preload/index.js` ✓\n\nThe main process should be able to find the preload at `dist/preload/index.js` since it's in the same output directory structure. Now I need to check how the main process actually references the preload file.","thinkingSignature":"0b1beed5799fb5ce4fa25ce3f8dad6a53458a56f05cbb409b6d0fe877eae946c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t4evkx29uggj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"preload\\|loadURL\\|loadFile\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/main/index.ts | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":131003,"output":272,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":150537,"cost":{"input":0.0393009,"output":0.00032639999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.040783019999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776165406855,"responseId":"062d551ef4fe5185e2f0fd1e6d7168b2"}}
