{"type":"message","id":"4a0acadf","parentId":"1e1cb2de","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:17:29.142Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Confirmed. `dist/main/preload.js` doesn't exist. The main process is looking for `dist/main/preload.js` but it's at `dist/preload/index.js`.\n\nI need to fix this. The options are:\n1. Change the main/index.ts source to use `path.join(__dirname, '../preload/index.js')` - but this would only work if the preload file is named `index.js`\n2. Copy/link the preload to `dist/main/preload.js`3. Change the tsconfig to output preload to `dist/main/`\n4. The preload.ts source might have been `src/main/preload.ts` instead of `src/preload/index.ts`Actually, looking at the tsconfig.main.json - it includes both `src/main/**/*` and `src/preload/**/*`, and rootDir is `src` and outDir is `dist`. So:- `src/preload/index.ts` → `dist/preload/index.js` ✓But the main process at `src/main/index.ts` line 88 says `path.join(__dirname, 'preload.js')` which would look for `dist/main/preload.js`. \n\nWait, but actually looking at the electron docs, the `preload` option should be a path to a JS file. The `__dirname` in `dist/main/index.js` is `dist/main/`. So it looks for `dist/main/preload.js` which doesn't exist.\n\n\nThe simplest fix is to update the preload path in main/index.ts to point to `dist/preload/index.js` instead, since that's where TypeScript actually outputs it. Alternatively, I could add a post-build script to copy the preload file to the expected location, but adjusting the path is more straightforward.","thinkingSignature":"6963c2796f52219cd73a939d385880bd5de9795f353f1ecabbc39e330f670cbc"},{"type":"text","text":"🔴 **P0 启动失败：main/index.ts 找 `dist/main/preload.js`，但 preload 实际在 `dist/preload/index.js`。**\n\n修复 main/index.ts 的 preload 路径：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e6nk9y5ya20c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '85,92p' /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/main/index.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages"