{"type":"message","id":"e41500b6","parentId":"2b37944f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:21:29.358Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `build/` directory doesn't exist (no icon). The `dist/` structure is complete:- `dist/main/` - main process code- `dist/preload/` - preload script- `dist/renderer/` - renderer code (HTML + assets)The `build/` directory is only needed for packaging (icons), not for running in dev mode. Since we can't run the Electron app in WSL anyway (no display), let me focus on what's needed for the user to actually run the app on Windows.For the app to work on Windows:1. TypeScript compilation ✅ (dist/main, dist/preload, dist/renderer are all there)2. Vite build ✅ 3. \n\nPreload path is now fixed ✅. For development mode, the user would need concurrently installed so `npm run dev` works in one terminal. Let me verify that's available.","thinkingSignature":"2bfc0b7ff47808088df1488f033e2d6fd53ca2f5500f8d288418677314b8f2d3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_crcmfb9xws9x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/node_modules/concurrently/ 2>/dev/null && echo \"✅ concurrently已安装\" || echo \"❌ concurrently未安装\"\necho \"\"\nls /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/node_modules/electron/ 2>/dev/null | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":135372,"output":264,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":154898,"cost":{"input":0.0406116,"output":0.0003168,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.042084119999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776165678382,"responseId":"062d562db4990d72121386bf2cce76cb"}}
