{"type":"message","id":"5951721d","parentId":"7b13c6bd","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:21:45.130Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. `concurrently` is installed and `electron` is also installed. Now let me check if there's an issue with the `loadFile` in production mode.Looking at the main process source:```javascript\nif (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {\n  await mainWindow?.loadURL('http://localhost:5173')\n  mainWindow?.webContents.openDevTools()\n} else {\n  await mainWindow?.loadFile(path.join(__dirname, '../renderer/index.html'))\n}\n```In production, it loads `dist/renderer/index.html`. The path `path.join(__dirname, '../renderer/index.html')` = `dist/main/../renderer/index.html` = `dist/renderer/index.html`. \n\nThat resolves correctly to `dist/renderer/index.html`. Now I'm thinking through the different ways the user could actually run this—they could use `npm run dev` with concurrently for development, which requires the dev server running on port 5173, or they could build and package the app with `npm run dist` to create a Windows executable. The Windows build will need an icon file at `build/icon.ico` that doesn't currently exist, which will cause electron-builder to fail.\n\nLet me first check if the `npm run dev` command actually works as expected, then I'll need to address the icon issue. The icon can be a minimal placeholder since Windows will use a default if it's missing or corrupted. I should also investigate whether there are any runtime issues with the app that might prevent it from launching properly.","thinkingSignature":"84a94a96a49d12eab9c401db11d913636d2b2b8b9ca490bcf7c1834538d3ce36"},{"type":"text","text":"🔴 **发现阻断问题：`build/` 目录缺失，electron-builder 无法打包。**\n\n先检查实际运行时有没有其他代码问题：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e1yvhyd8phk6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 检查 preload 导出的 API 是否完整 ===\"\ngrep \"contextBridge.exposeInMainWorld\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/preload/index.t