{"type":"message","id":"4b9be180","parentId":"fc918f23","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:22:00.491Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, there's one big `contextBridge.exposeInMainWorld('electronAPI', {...})` call that exposes all the APIs. That should be fine.Let me now create the build directory with a minimal icon to allow electron-builder to work. Actually, we can just create the directory and the app will use a default icon. Let me also check if the issue is just the missing build directory.Actually, the most important thing right now is: can the user run the app in development mode?For `npm run dev` to work:\n1. `concurrently` ✅ installed\n2. `npm run dev:renderer` starts vite dev server on port 5173 ✅\n3. `npm run dev:electron` compiles and runs electron ✅But there's a timing issue - `npm run dev` runs both concurrently, but the electron process will try to load `http://localhost:5173` immediately while vite might not be ready yet.Also, for the production build (`npm run dist`):\n\n\nThe build directory is missing, which will cause the electron-builder to fail when it tries to create the Windows executable. I need to set up a minimal build setup with at least a placeholder icon file.","thinkingSignature":"1e844fd35ac4a2ff0c1de761c1f74a48ec2e3a176f5b5744acb85e4a645b2601"},{"type":"text","text":"`npm run dist` 无法打包因为 `build/` 目录不存在。创建必要的构建配置：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9l2hwxc11m9z_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/build\necho \"=== 检查是否有任何图标文件 ===\"\nfind /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs -name \"*.ico\" -o -name \"*.icns\" 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":136401,"output":350,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":156013,"cost":{"input":0.0409203,"output":0.00041999999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.042496019999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776165710265