{"type":"message","id":"4fec657e","parentId":"fd1ae4e8","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:30:54.751Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The electron-builder failed because it tried to download Electron headers from the internet (www.electronjs.org) and the request timed out. This is a network issue in the WSL environment, not a code bug.\n\nThe `sharp` native module is causing the build to fail because it requires recompilation for the Electron version, and it needs to download headers from the internet.\n\nThe solution is to either:\n1. Remove the `sharp` dependency (which is used for image processing in `@xenova/transformers`)\n2. Or use `@electron/rebuild` with pre-cached headers\n\nBut actually, `sharp` is a dependency of `@xenova/transformers`. Let me check if `sharp` is actually needed or if it's an optional dependency.\n \nLooking at the actual build error more carefully, the issue is that electron-builder is attempting to rebuild `sharp` from source and fetching headers from the internet, which fails in WSL. The best approach here is to add `sharp` to the `build.ignored` option in electron-builder config so it skips rebuilding that native module during the packaging process.","thinkingSignature":"9235006b58132f7bf20928eed8b181762770fd9d550a229e01b1dbbfad0e7ccc"},{"type":"text","text":"electron-builder 在 WSL 环境里下载 Electron  headers 超时（网络问题）。同时 `sharp` 原生模块需要在线编译。\n\n解决方案：把 `sharp` 设为可选依赖，打包时忽略它：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kow0vfdqdhkx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '54,72p' /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/package.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34531,"output":317,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54110,"cost":{"input":0.0103593,"output":0.0003804,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01189542}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776166244830,"responseId":"062d58648674c4ee30517b7ac0ed6156"}}
