{"type":"message","id":"00e30b7a","parentId":"67ec8c3b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:35:46.114Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear now: electron-builder is trying to download Electron from GitHub releases, but the WSL environment has network issues accessing github.com (EOF error). \n\nThis is a network/environment issue, not a code issue. The WSL can't download from GitHub reliably.\n\nThe key question: is the user on Windows or in WSL? If they're on Windows, they should run `npm run dist` on Windows directly, not in WSL. If they're in WSL, they need internet access to download Electron.\n\nLet me check if there's already an Electron binary cached locally that we can use.","thinkingSignature":"0f738b01708a81f786ad0c59a787aaa6d53d85998b25167d0c408243207cda8e"},{"type":"text","text":"WSL 网络问题，无法从 GitHub 下载 Electron 二进制文件。这是环境限制，不是代码问题。\n\n**检查本地是否已有 Electron 缓存：**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0um4iql7vs5g_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.cache/electron -name \"electron\" -type f 2>/dev/null | head -5\necho \"---\"\nfind /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/node_modules/electron/dist -name \"electron\" -type f 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":45931,"output":238,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65431,"cost":{"input":0.0137793,"output":0.0002856,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01522062}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776166538835,"responseId":"062d598a6fc203711dba1db0819422c3"}}
