{"type":"message","id":"020a9677","parentId":"514d3f18","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:35:54.311Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Electron binary exists in node_modules. The issue is that electron-builder wants to download a specific version (v41.1.1) for packaging, but it's trying to get it from GitHub.\n\nLet me try to configure electron-builder to use the locally installed Electron instead of downloading it. I can set `electronDist` or use `ELECTRON_MIRROR`.\n\nActually, the best approach here is to set the `ELECTRON_MIRROR` environment variable to use a Chinese mirror for faster/successful downloads in China.\n\nOr better yet, let me check if there's a way to make electron-builder use the local electron.\n\n\nActually, I'm realizing the core issue: electron-builder v26 requires downloading an Electron binary even for `--dir` packaging, but the Windows environment would have internet access while WSL doesn't. I could try setting `ELECTRON_SKIP_BINARY_DOWNLOAD=1` or use a mirror like `https://npmmirror.com/mirrors/electron/` to bypass the download requirement entirely.","thinkingSignature":"d056c6ef0d332924ade57897c5ddefbd7cffde136614d706da04655063379b3a"},{"type":"text","text":"Electron 已安装在 node_modules 里，但 electron-builder 想下载指定版本做打包。设置国内镜像加速：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kr8z111aj8b0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs && ELECTRON_MIRROR=\"https://npmmirror.com/mirrors/electron/\" npm run pack 2>&1","timeout":300}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46203,"output":298,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65763,"cost":{"input":0.013860899999999999,"output":0.00035759999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015374219999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776166546206,"responseId":"062d5991390e7692face43111e917adc"}}
