{"type":"message","id":"97fff8b4","parentId":"f599819d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T12:12:24.838Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is clear: `winCodeSign` tool (for code signing the Windows executable) can't be downloaded from GitHub due to network issues. The user needs to either:\n1. Use a different approach that doesn't require winCodeSign\n2. Set up a mirror for electron-builder-binaries tools\n\nThe `winCodeSign` is used to add a digital signature to the Windows executable. For a portable exe, we can disable this step by setting `windows.signAndEditExecutable: false` or by using `portable` target which doesn't require code signing.\n\nLet me fix the package.json to disable the Windows code signing requirement.","thinkingSignature":"10ce4663580e828cd3f5d2fcf03eb473553d8bbf050e2d0558c0d310de205e6f"},{"type":"text","text":"原因找到了：`winCodeSign`（Windows 代码签名工具）下载超时。这是打包 Windows exe 的最后一步，可以跳过。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2ccc79rprnz1_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/package.json","edits":[{"oldText":"    \"win\": {\n      \"target\": \"portable\"\n    },","newText":"    \"win\": {\n      \"target\": \"portable\",\n      \"signAndEditExecutable\": false\n    },"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":258,"cacheRead":79866,"cacheWrite":14999,"totalTokens":95177,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0003096,"cacheRead":0.00479196,"cacheWrite":0.005624625,"total":0.010742385}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776168734894,"responseId":"062d621e565a6cbfe9ab4329379da8fe"}}
