{"type":"message","id":"e282a731","parentId":"f6b813b1","timestamp":"2026-04-14T12:13:15.759Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a different approach - set the ELECTRON_BUILDER_BINARIES_MIRROR environment variable to use the npmmirror for all electron-builder binaries.\n\nActually, looking at the electron-builder docs, the option is:\n```\nELECTRON_BUILDER_BINARIES_MIRROR=https://npmmirror.com/mirrors/electron-builder-binaries/\n```\n\nBut this might not be the right URL for npmmirror. Let me try setting it directly as an environment variable in the build command.\n\nActually, let me check if we can just use the `nsis` target without code signing. For nsis, we can set `createDesktopShortcut: false` and `createStartMenuShortcut: false` to skip some signing steps. But the rcedit step (resource editing) still runs.\n \nI think the real issue is that electron-builder tries to download winCodeSign during resource editing even when we don't need it. The rcedit step is mandatory for Windows builds since it embeds metadata like the app name into the executable. Without an icon specified, it might skip that part, but I should try configuring the mirror URL directly instead.\n\nLet me see if I can set `electronDownload` to use the npmmirror for all binaries, not just Electron itself.\n\nActually, the portable target should work without winCodeSign—I just need to try building with `npm run pack` using the portable target instead.","thinkingSignature":"08317599e269140758324d6d9704e2d7fa28f54ea0e79e6332f8cf9582b51c3c"},{"type":"text","text":"试试直接在 Windows 上运行，配置镜像解决 winCodeSign 下载问题：\n\n**在 Windows 终端运行：**\n```cmd\nset ELECTRON_BUILDER_BINARIES_MIRROR=https://npmmirror.com/mirrors/electron-builder-binaries/\nnpm run dist\n```\n\n或者如果你觉得麻烦，直接用 **`npm run pack`** 替代，它生成 `win-unpacked` 文件夹，里面有可以直接双击运行的 `番茄创作工作台.exe`，只是没有打包成单文件便携版。\n\n---\n\n**两个选择：**\n\n| 命令 | 输出 | 是否需要 winCodeSign |\n|------|------|---------------------|\n| `npm run