{"type":"message","id":"1618a694","parentId":"2b104dde","timestamp":"2026-04-14T12:19:29.971Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that Windows blocked the executable from running. This is a common issue with unsigned Electron apps - Windows SmartScreen will block executables that aren't signed with a code signing certificate.\n\nThis is expected behavior for an unsigned Electron app. The app is not signed, so Windows SmartScreen will block it. This is not a code bug - it's a security feature.\n\nThe user needs to either:\n1. Click \"More info\" and \"Run anyway\" to bypass the block\n2. Get a code signing certificate (expensive)\n3. Submit the app to Microsoft for SmartScreen reputation\n\nLet me explain this simply.","thinkingSignature":"e04e95fc8be0edc7b6cc5a26e324b2f42ab99db702dda3717faadd67b9e50f22"},{"type":"text","text":"这是 Windows SmartScreen 的正常防护，未签名的 exe 都会被拦。\n\n**解决方法：运行exe时点「更多信息」→「仍要运行」：**\n\n```\n[被阻止画面]\n  ↓\n点击「更多信息」\n  ↓\n出现「仍要运行」按钮\n  ↓\n点它就能启动了\n```\n\n一次性操作，以后有签名就不拦了。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":202,"cacheRead":95659,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95861,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0.00024239999999999998,"cacheRead":0.00573954,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00598194}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776169157475,"responseId":"062d63c571d2165da25e664afb74aa3d"}}
