{"type":"message","id":"81c908bb","parentId":"f9e6a137","timestamp":"2026-04-14T12:25:28.523Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the current file content is indeed:\n```\n    .replace(/\\/g, '/')\n    .replace(/\\/+/g, '/')\n```\n\nBut esbuild says line 11 is `.replace(/\\/g, '/')` with \"Unterminated string literal\". This is because in regex `/\\/g`, the `\\/` means \"escaped forward slash\" - but then the regex ends with `/g`. However, the regex literal is `/\\/g` which should be valid (matches forward slash).\n\nWait, let me re-read the error carefully:\n```\n 9  |      .filter(Boolean)\n10  |      .join('/')\n\n\n11  |      .replace(/\\/g, '/')\n12  |      .replace(/\\/+/g, '/')\n```\n\nError at line 11 column 23: Unterminated string literal.\n\nColumn 23 on line 11 would be around the `g` in `'/')`. But that's a string, not a regex. Unless... wait, the issue is the regex `/\\/g` - this is supposed to be a regex literal matching a forward slash. But in the context of a `.replace()` call, it's `.replace(/\\/g, '/')`. The regex is `/\\/g` - which would be parsed as... `\\` followed by `/`... \n\nAh, I see the problem now. The regex `/\\/g` is trying to match a forward slash, but the backslash is escaping it in a way that confuses the parser. The regex literal syntax `/\\/g` is invalid because the backslash escapes the forward slash, but then there's nothing to close the regex properly - the second `/` gets interpreted as the closing delimiter, leaving `g` as unexpected text. I need to double-escape the backslash so the regex engine receives a literal backslash to match against the forward slash. The fix is to use `.replace(/\\\\/g, '/')` which correctly represents a regex matching a single backslash character. I'm working through how JavaScript string literals encode backslashes—when I write `\\\\` in a string, it becomes a single backslash character. So `replace(/\\\\/g, '/')` passes a regex containing two backslashes to the replace method, which should then match a single backslash in the actual string. But my file shows something different, so I need to check what's actually written there.\n\nLooking at the error message more carefully, the caret is pointing at column 23 on line 11, which should be around the closing quote of the replacement string. Let me count the exact column position to figure out what's actually at that location. I think I've found the issue - in a regex literal, `\\/` is a valid escape for a forward slash, so `/\\/g` should theoretically parse as a regex matching `/`. But the real problem is that `\\/` in the regex is being interpreted as an escaped forward slash, which means the regex never actually matches anything, and the replacement doesn't work as intended.\n\nThe simplest solution is to bypass regex entirely and just use string splitting and joining to replace backslashes with forward slashes, which avoids all these escaping complications. I see the issue now - the error message is showing `/\\/g` with only one backslash in the representation, but in the actual source code there must be two backslashes that got collapsed during display. When I count the characters in `.replace(/\\/g, '/')`, the caret at column 23 lands on the first quote of the replacement string `'/')`, which suggests the regex pattern itself is malformed or incomplete.\n\nLooking at the regex `/\\/g`, I can see it starts with `/`, then has a backslash-escaped forward slash `\\/`, followed by `g` and the closing delimiter - but there's nothing after the closing `/` to indicate what flags are present, which is why the regex parsing is failing.\n\nI think the file actually contains `\\\\/` as two separate characters (backslash and forward slash), which would make the regex `/\\//g` (matching a forward slash with the global flag), but when esbuild displays it, it shows as `/\\/g`. If that's the case, then the regex is actually valid - it's matching forward slashes globally. The real issue might be that esbuild is having trouble parsing this particular regex syntax, or there's a mismatch between what I think is in the file and what's actually there. The replace call with the regex `/\\/g` is actually valid—it's matching forward slashes and replacing them with forward slashes, which is a no-op. I should just try the string split/join approach instead to see if that resolves the esbuild error.","thinkingSignature":"07a3bf895a85e4ee5d7d2e8bf566af67a18a8b11544460fb38db4c0c20f5c30f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4615makzot60_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/renderer/src/components/OutlineTree.tsx","content":"import { useState, useEffect } from 'react'\nimport { Tree, Spin, Empty, message } from 'antd'\nimport { FileOutlined, FolderOutlined } from '@ant-design/icons'\nimport type { DataNode } from 'antd/es/tree'\n\n// 浏览器环境下替代 path.join 的工具函数\nconst pathJoin = (...parts: string[]): string => {\n  return parts.filter(Boolean).join('/')\n}\n\ninterface OutlineTreeProps {\n  projectRoot: string\n  activeChapter: string | null\n  onSelect: (filePath: string) => void\n}\n\ninterface FileEntry {\n  name: string\n  isDirectory: boolean\n  isFile: boolean\n  path: string\n  children?: FileEntry[]\n}\n\nconst OutlineTree = ({ projectRoot, activeChapter, onSelect }: OutlineTreeProps) => {\n  const [treeData, setTreeData] = useState<DataNode[]>([])\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false)\n  const [expandedKeys, setExpandedKeys] = useState<React.Key[]>([])\n\n  // 读取目录结构\n  const loadDirectory = async (dirPath: string): Promise<FileEntry[]> => {\n    try {\n      const entries = await window.electronAPI.readdir(dirPath)\n      if (!Array.isArray(entries)) return []\n\n      const result: FileEntry[] = []\n\n      for (const entry of entries) {\n        const fullPath = pathJoin(dirPath, entry.name)\n\n        if (entry.isDirectory) {\n          const children = await loadDirectory(fullPath)\n          result.push({\n            name: entry.name,\n            isDirectory: true,\n            isFile: false,\n            path: fullPath,\n            children\n          })\n        } else if (entry.isFile && entry.name.endsWith('.md')) {\n          result.push({\n            name: entry.name.replace('.md', ''),\n            isDirectory: false,\n            isFile: true,\n            path: fullPath\n          })\n        }\n      }\n\n      return result.sort((a, b) => {\n        if (a.isDirectory && !b.isDirectory) return -1\n        if (!a.isDirectory && b.isDirectory) return 1\n        return a.name.localeCompare(b.name)\n      })\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error('读取目录失败:', error)\n      return []\n    }\n  }\n\n  // 转换为 Ant Design Tree 需要的格式\n  const convertToTreeData = (entries: FileEntry[], parentKey: string = ''): DataNode[] => {\n    return entries.map((entry, index) => {\n      const key = parentKey ? `${parentKey}-${index}` : `${index}`\n\n      if (entry.isDirectory && entry.children) {\n        return {\n          title: entry.name,\n          key,\n          icon: <FolderOutlined />,\n          children: convertToTreeData(entry.children, key),\n          isLeaf: false\n        }\n      } else {\n        return {\n          title: entry.name,\n          key: entry.path,\n          icon: <FileOutlined />,\n          isLeaf: true\n        }\n      }\n    })\n  }\n\n  // 加载大纲\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const loadOutline = async () => {\n      if (!projectRoot) return\n\n      setLoading(true)\n      try {\n        const plotsDir = pathJoin(projectRoot, 'plots')\n        const exists = await window.electronAPI.exists(plotsDir)\n        if (!exists) {\n          await window.electronAPI.mkdir(plotsDir)\n          setTreeData([])\n          return\n        }\n\n        const entries = await loadDirectory(plotsDir)\n        const data = convertToTreeData(entries)\n        setTreeData(data)\n\n        const getAllKeys = (nodes: DataNode[]): string[] => {\n          let keys: string[] = []\n          nodes.forEach(node => {\n            keys.push(node.key as string)\n            if (node.children) keys = keys.concat(getAllKeys(node.children))\n          })\n          return keys\n        }\n        setExpandedKeys(getAllKeys(data))\n      } catch (error) {\n        message.error('加载大纲失败')\n        console.error(error)\n      } finally {\n        setLoading(false)\n      }\n    }\n\n    loadOutline()\n  }, [projectRoot])\n\n  // 监听文件变化，自动刷新大纲\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!projectRoot) return\n\n    const plotsDir = pathJoin(projectRoot, 'plots')\n    window.electronAPI.fsWatch(plotsDir)\n\n    const removeListener = window.electronAPI.onFsChange(() => {\n      loadDirectory(pathJoin(projectRoot, 'plots')).then(entries => {\n        const data = convertToTreeData(entries)\n        setTreeData(data)\n      })\n    })\n\n    return () => {\n      removeListener()\n      window.electronAPI.fsUnwatch()\n    }\n  }, [projectRoot])\n\n  // 处理选择\n  const handleSelect = (selectedKeys: React.Key[]) => {\n    if (selectedKeys.length === 0) return\n    const key = String(selectedKeys[0])\n    if (key.startsWith('/') || key.includes('.md')) {\n      onSelect(key)\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (loading) {\n    return (\n      <div style={{ padding: 20, textAlign: 'center' }}>\n        <Spin tip=\"加载中...\" />\n      </div>\n    )\n  }\n\n  if (treeData.length === 0) {\n    return (\n      <div style={{ padding: 20 }}>\n        <Empty\n          description=\"暂无章节\"\n          image={Empty.PRESENTED_IMAGE_SIMPLE}\n        />\n      </div>\n    )\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <div style={{ height: '100%', overflow: 'auto', padding: 10 }}>\n      <Tree\n        treeData={treeData}\n        expandedKeys={expandedKeys}\n        selectedKeys={activeChapter ? [activeChapter] : []}\n        onSelect={handleSelect}\n        onExpand={setExpandedKeys}\n        showIcon\n        defaultExpandAll\n      />\n    </div>\n  )\n}\n\nexport default OutlineTree\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":87806,"output":2301,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109369,"cost":{"input":0.0263418,"output":0.0027611999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.030258719999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776169476226,"responseId":"062d650438a99576beb9ed363c9bdc96"}}
