{"type":"message","id":"5418697c","parentId":"09474250","timestamp":"2026-04-14T12:28:17.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The db/index.ts uses `window.electronAPI.yaml.read/write` which are properly exposed in the preload. Let me check if the preload yaml handlers return the right format.\n\nLooking at the preload:\n```typescript\nyaml: {\n  read: (filePath: string) => ipcRenderer.invoke('yaml:read', filePath),\n  write: (filePath: string, data: any) => ipcRenderer.invoke('yaml:write', filePath, data),\n}\n```\n\nAnd in the electron.d.ts:\n```typescript\nyaml: {\n  read: (filePath: string) => Promise<{ success: boolean; data?: unknown; error?: string }>\n\n\n```\n\nSo `window.electronAPI.yaml.read()` returns `{ success: boolean; data?: unknown; error?: string }`. The db/index.ts destructures `result.content` for files, but the yaml API actually returns `result.data`, not `result.content`. This is a bug that would cause `characters_facts` to be undefined when the code tries to use it.","thinkingSignature":"79d53ae26bacc2d390488721baa00fa30a5934f34c8be972350567d63fdff2c5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l2y8b5umrszq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '30,50p' /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/renderer/src/db/index.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91211,"output":264,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110737,"cost":{"input":0.0273633,"output":0.0003168,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.028835819999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776169689317,"responseId":"062d65d9d74cf888fbcba0ad85e89b1b"}}
